title: zucchini casserole
directions: In bowl, manually stir together cooled zucchini, soup, cheese, sour cream, carrot and onion.
In pan, melt butter; add stuffing mix.
In greased casserole dish, put one layer zucchini mix and half of stuffing mix.
Add rest of zucchini mix and top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, syrup and butter. Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour in two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 3 hours before serving.

title: bread and butter pickles with carrots
directions: Combine onions, peppers, carrots and cucumbers.
Mix in salt. Cover with ice and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pickle mixture.
Bring to a bubbling boil and boil 1 minute.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: cranberry sauce salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Chill and fold in other ingredients.

title: italian beef
directions: Brown roast on top of stove in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer all day (or until tender).
Refrigerate overnight.	Spoon
off
fat and slice meat.
Reheat meat in juice. Brush
submarine
bread with juice.
Peppers may be served. Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Stew and cut the hen into bite sized pieces.
To the broth that the chicken has been cooked in, add the noodles, pepper, onion and celery.
Cook until noodles are tender.
To this, add sauce made from flour, milk and butter.
Combine with noodle mixture the chicken, mushroom soup and the cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 12.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let stand overnight.
Delicious on ham, hot dogs, Swiss cheese and mustard sandwiches.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and evaporated milk.
Add and mix well the flour, baking powder, 1/4 and 1 teaspoon salt and vanilla.
Blend in poppy seed.
Makes 3 mini loaves.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift the flour, salt and cayenne pepper together.
Then cut in the margarine until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
Stir in the finely grated cheese and blend together with the egg yolk and water into a firm dough.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into thin fingers 1/4-inch wide. (Or may be shaped with a cookie press.)
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger crescent delight
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press in baking dish, smashing flat at seams and bringing up on sides 1-inch.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Stir in undiluted chili mix.
Pour meat mixture in baking dish over crescent rolls.
Cover with grated cheeses and bake in 350° oven.

title: ginger spiced chicken
directions: Saute chicken and garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Stir in peppers and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until crisp-tender.
Combine water, cornstarch and soy sauce in a small bowl, stirring until smooth.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Add ginger and bouillon cube. Stir in nuts.
Cook and continue to stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with rice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread dough over pan.
Cook according to directions.
Mix remaining ingredients except fruit and spread over crust.
Top with fruit.

title: eva's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and roll out to rise for 2 to 3 hours.
May be kept in refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute the onions and carrots in the butter until soft.
Cook the potatoes in the chicken bouillon cube and water until soft. Stir flour in onions and carrots.
Mix all together.
Add milk and simmer until heated through.

title: egg fluff
directions: Whip eggs lightly.
Dot pan with margarine.
Sprinkle cheese on bottom.
Add bacon.
Combine salt and pepper, mustard and half and half.
Pour half of this mixture over cheese.
Add eggs.
Add remaining mixture of half and half and spices.
Bake about 350 degrees until set, about 40 minutes.
Serves 9-12 people.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: In heavy sauce pan over low heat, melt chips with condensed milk, salt, butter and marshmallows.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Spread evenly onto wax paper lined 8-9 inch square pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off paper, cut into squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: mocha cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, mix crumbs, sugar and margarine.
In buttered 9-inch spring-form or 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pat crumbs firmly on bottom and sides and chill.

title: bonnie butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 layer pans (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
In a large mixer bowl, mix the butter, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat 5 minutes on high speed, scraping the bowl occasionally.
On low speed, mix in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with the milk.
Pour into the pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: apple relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole dish
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place rice, soups and milk in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pieces of raw chicken on top, skin side up. Sprinkle one envelope of onion soup on top.
Completely cover with foil.
Bake 3 hours.
No peeking!
This is important.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cool.
Add all remaining ingredients, except whipped cream and cheese.
Let set in refrigerator until it begins to jell.
Soften cheese and whip cream.
Add cheese to cream and then add to jello mixture and return to refrigerator.
Place ingredients into square pan.
Cut into squares and serve as salad or desert.

title: l'abricot et amondes dessert
directions: Mix crushed wafers, melted butter, almonds and almond flavoring, reserving 1/3 c. for topping.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, press half of the mixture in the bottom firmly.
Add half of ice cream.
Put in freezer to refirm ice cream.
When firm, coat with about 10 oz. of apricot jam.
Repeat layers and top with reserved crumb mixture.
Freeze.
Cut in squares or serve in sherbet glasses and top each with a cherry, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: california paella
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until translucent in medium size pot.
Stir in broth; add water to make 2 cups (3 ounces).
Add rice and season packet.
Dump and stir.
Boil, cover, then simmer. Ten minutes before rice is ready, add shrimp; cover.
When shrimp and rice is done, add avocado*, tomato*, raisins*.
(*Do not cook these ingredients.)
Serve immediately with salad and French or Italian bread.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Cook time:
30 minutes.

title: greek macaroni salad
directions: Combine in large bowl the first 7 ingredients.
Prepare a dressing with the remaining ingredients and pour over the first mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: corn griddle cakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat eggs, add milk and oil and add to flour mixture.
Stir until well blended. Heat griddle, heavy frying pan or electric skillet slowly until moderately hot.
Grease very lightly before cooking each batch. Ladle or pour about 1/4 cup batter for each cake.
Cook until top side is full of bubbles that begin to break and edges are dry. Turn, brown other side.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen 4 to 5-inch cakes or 1 dozen 6 to 7-inch cakes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with 1 gallon water and 1 cup lime.
Soak 24 hours.
Wash three times.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Pack in jars; seal.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter until well blended and smooth. Add sugars and beat until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Roll dough into balls and roll balls in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet (ungreased) and bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Place 1 kiss in middle of each cookie and bake for 2 more minutes.
Freeze before stacking.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Mix ingredients in a separate bowl.
Melt butter at bottom of pan.
Cook noodles and add cheese, sour cream, sugar, cinnamon and eggs.
Pour into pan with butter on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hold-the-sugar apple pie
directions: Measure about 1/4 cup concentrate into small bowl; stir in cornstarch and spices.
Place the remainder of the concentrate into a large skillet with the apples.
Simmer gently until apples are just tender.
Lightly stir in cornstarch mixture until quite thick.
Stir in butter.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell; top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in three layers.

title: almond pumpkin bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice and salt in medium bowl.
Beat eggs, pumpkin, sugar, evaporated milk and oil in large mixer bowl until blended.
Add flour mixture and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Mix just until moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pan.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed; stir. Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours (5 to 6 hours on high heat).

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies in half and layer in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (filling side up).
Prepare pudding and pour over Twinkies. Crush 4 candy bars and sprinkle over pudding layer.
Place remaining layer of Twinkies (filling side down). Spread top with Cool Whip. Crush last candy bar and sprinkle over top.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble, reserving 1/4 cup fat.
Cook onion in reserved fat until tender.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and dash of pepper.
Add vinegar and 1 cup of water; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add bacon, potatoes and eggs.
Heat thoroughly, tossing lightly. Garnish with parsley, pimiento and bacon curls.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
While hot, frost with:

title: piccalilli
directions: Slice all vegetables fine.
Alternate vegetables and salt in layers.
Let stand overnight.

title: clam-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and save.
Place caps, rounded side down, on broiler pan.
Drain liquid from clams and reserve.
In skillet, over medium heat, melt butter and brush some on caps.
In remaining butter, cook chopped stems, garlic and clam liquid for 5 minutes.
Stir in clams and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into caps and broil 8 minutes or until tender.

title: bush's batch
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt onto waxed paper or small bowl.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugars and egg until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in hot water and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture until blended and smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Fill a deep fat fryer or skillet with oil to a 2-inch depth. Heat to 375°.
Meanwhile, combine milk and egg in a mixing bowl. Stir together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture; blend well. Fold in zucchini.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonful into hot oil. Fry until deep golden brown, turning once.
Drain thoroughly on paper towels.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and butter in saucepan.
Heat to boiling point.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool. Stir in marshmallows and cracker crumbs.
Spread into foil lined 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
Heat butterscotch bits and peanut butter on low heat.
Add vanilla; spread over crumb mixture. Refrigerate.
Cut into bars.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large mixing bowl add Wesson oil and eggs.
Beat, then add sugar gradually and beat until well mixed.
Add dry ingredients and carrots, mix well.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans which have been oiled and floured.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: red punch
directions: Put half of the first 4 ingredients into 2 gallon jugs.
Add water until full.
When serving, add sherbet (about half) and half of ginger ale.
You may freeze green cherries and lemon slices in part of the punch to float on top.

title: popsicle
directions: Stir all ingredients together, then put into popsicle molds. Freeze.

title: shepherd's skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, brown ground beef.
Stir in carrots, 1 cup water and onion soup mix.
Cover and cook over low heat until carrots are almost tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in noodles, tomatoes, corn, 1 cup water, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat until noodles and vegetables are tender, about 8 minutes, stirring several times. If needed, to prevent sticking, stir in 2 or 3 tablespoons water.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Melt butter and pour into a Bundt pan.
Add some nuts, a sprinkle of sugar and a sprinkle of cinnamon.
Roll each section of biscuit into a ball.
Lay in the pan.
When all the biscuits are in place, pour the remaining mixture of sugar, cinnamon, nuts and butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured 8-inch round layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
In a separate small bowl, beat together egg and buttermilk, then add to margarine/sugar until well mixed.
Combine in a mixing bowl the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix together dry and wet ingredients alternating in small amounts until well mixed. Add raisins and caraway seed to batter.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(If a glass loaf pan is used, reduce temperature to 325°.)
Test for doneness with a pick in center that comes out clean.
Yield:
1 large (9 x 5-inch) loaf.

title: apple plum crisp
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter, 1/4 cup brown sugar, lemon juice, flour and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add apples and plums.
Toss to coat. Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: tofu patties
directions: Mash chickpeas with fork or crush in food processor.
Do same with tofu.
Add the other ingredients.
Make into patties.
Bake on cookie sheet that's oiled.
Can also fry.
In case mixture is too soft, add more cracker meal.
Makes 12 patties.

title: french hamburger (bitoque)
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk. Squeeze to remove excess milk. Combine crumbs, beef, salt and pepper. Mix well. Form into about 6 flat patties. Flour the patties. Heat butter in a large skillet. Add patties and cook for 5 minutes or more on each side until done.

title: candy apple walnut pie
directions: In a large bowl, toss apples, walnuts, cinnamon candies, 1/3 cup of sugar and flour.
Pour into one frozen pie crust.
Break or crumble second frozen crust into very small pieces; toss with remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in preheated oven on a preheated baking sheet 55 to 60 minutes or until candies melt and bubble up through the crumbled crust.
Cool completely before serving.
Serves 8.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and sugar together. Blend in eggs, add that to the other ingredient.
Pour on to unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: nutritious, delicious baked apples
directions: Peel top third of apple.
Remove core, leaving bottom intact to be filled.
Mix pineapple, raisins, honey and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spoon mixture evenly into each apple.
Place apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle dash of cinnamon over each filled apple. Pour apple juice around apples to a depth of 1/2-inch.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Baste with more juice to keep apples moist.
Keep baking until apples are tender, but not mushy.
Serve warm or chilled.
Top with low-fat whipped topping or vanilla yogurt.

title: german potato-buttercream eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If mixture is too stiff, add milk.
If mixture is too moist, add more sugar.
If desired, add cherries, candied fruits or nuts or flavoring.
Shape and refrigerate overnight.
Dip in melted chocolate and decorate as desired.
Excellent!

title: nut bread
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Add sugar and nuts.
Beat egg. Mix with milk and add dry ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Pour into pan lined with wax paper.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over a wood fire for about 2 weeks.
Season.
This will serve about 3,801 people. If more are expected, add the 2 rabbits, but do so only if necessary, as most people don't like to find hare in their stew.

title: chocolate chip custard
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well by hand.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until firm.

title: pumpkin bars(makes 40 two inch squares)
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl. Combine flour, baking soda, spices, baking powder and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 11 1/4 x 17 1/4 x 3-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl.
Mix well and chill.
Before serving, mold into desired shape and top with cocktail sauce. Serve with assorted crackers, breadsticks, etc.

title: banana brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. In a large bowl with a mixer set at low speed, blend flour, sugar and margarine until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Blend in baking powder.
Stir in egg and bananas.
Gently fold in chocolate pieces and lemon rind.
Add a little milk if batter is stiff. Spread mixture in baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tester or wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind or chop the cabbage, tomatoes and onions.
Mix and cook until tender. Mix the sugar, salt and flour.
Add the vinegar and mustard.
Mix well and stir into cooked vegetables.
Bring it all to a boil.
Remove from heat and put into clean, hot jars.
Cook for 5 minutes at 5 pounds of pressure.
Makes 10 pints.

title: oregon apple pie
directions: Place apples in bottom of pie pan.
Sprinkle on cinnamon and sugar.
Place flour in a large bowl; mix with melted butter, eggs and pecans.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Can also check with a toothpick (insert toothpick into center of pie and remove; it if comes out clean, it's done).
Let pie cool.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: monterey jack with pasta
directions: Cook macaroni according to package; drain.
In saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Off heat, stir in milk, keeping smooth.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and boiling.
Spread 1/2 cooked macaroni over bottom of buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese. Layer with remaining macaroni.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Pour hot sauce evenly over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs very well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press 3 or 4 additional M&M's in each cookie.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In an 8-quart kettle, cover soup bone (cut into pieces) with water and cook 3 to 4 hours.
Remove bone and add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly until vegetables are done.
Remove meat from bone, cut into bite size pieces and add to soup.
Do not skim broth.
Add water if some has cooked away.
This soup improves with cooling and reheating.
Freezes well, too.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken, onion and peppers.
Cook and stir chicken until cooked through. Add corn, broth and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover until cheese melts.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine together for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and salt.
Mix and spread on cookie sheet.

title: squash souffle
directions: Steam onion and squash together until tender; drain excess water and mash well.
Add crackers, salt, pepper, butter, beaten egg yolks and cheese; blend well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake about 45 minutes or until set and slightly browned.

title: creme de menthe brownies no. 2
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Cool, do not cut.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Beat egg; add water and oil. Mix well.
Add liquids to dry ingredients, mixing with fork (more water may be needed to make batter).
Dredge onion rings through batter and deep fry until golden brown.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour soda water over dates and cherries.
Let cool while mixing sugar and butter with egg.
Add to date mixture.
Add flour and nuts and bake in loaf or muffin pan.
Serve with whipped cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan delights
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first four ingredients. Cook over medium heat until all sugar is dissolved. Gradually add milk and mix well. Continue cooking until candy thermometer reads 248° (firm ball stage). Remove from the heat. Stir in vanilla until blended. Fold in the pecans. Drop by tablespoons onto a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Chill until firm. Melt chocolate chips and shortening in a microwave-safe bowl or double boiler. Drizzle over each cluster. Cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange cubes in casserole dish.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over cubes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic. Arrange meat over mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dip for fruit tray
directions: Mix all ingredients and dip away.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into balls or fingers. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix
brown
sugar, white sugar and margarine.
Sift and add flour,
baking powder, soda, salt and eggs.
Add vanilla, vinegar, nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda. Make a well.
Add oil, water, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Fill floured, well-greased 1-pound coffee cans about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool completely before removing from cans.
Bread may be baked in pans instead of cans.

title: island crab cakes
directions: Soak bread in milk and egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Make patties and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides. Use a cast iron skillet.
If you like spicy, you may add Old Bay Seasoning or Texas Pete sauce.
Serves 6-8.

title: cheesecake
directions: Freeze Pet milk until soft like ice cream.
Mix Jell-O, hot water and pineapple.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Crush graham crackers.
Mix with melted butter and powdered sugar and press in large pan.
Beat Pet milk until stiff.
Add cream cheese and sugar mixture, then Jell-O mixture.
Pour into crust.
Let stand in icebox overnight.

title: pizza heroes
directions: Split bread in half lengthwise; toast under broiler, then spread with butter or margarine.
Spread pizza sauce on cut surfaces of bread.
Roll up salami slices jelly roll fashion; place 10 rolls on each half.
Lay cheese strips diagonally across salami.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Mix together oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Combine both mixtures and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool before removing from pan.

title: congealed pineapple salad
directions: Combine sugar and pineapple in saucepan.
Bring to boil; remove from heat and add jello until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk.
Stir.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Save a few nuts for top.

title: open faced tuna sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, combine tuna, apple, onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice and pepper.
Spread on bread.
Top with a cheese slice.
Broil about 4 inches from the heat for 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Yield:
4 sandwiches.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: thick and robust barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together on medium speed until well blended the first 3 ingredients.
Add 2 eggs.
Mix well.
Pour batter into graham cracker pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill while mixing next 3 ingredients.

Pour over graham cracker mixture. Slice the 3 bananas lengthwise and place on top of the mixture. Add one small can (well drained) crushed pineapple, 1 large tub Cool Whip, nuts and maraschino cherries; layering each in the order listed.
Keep refrigerated.

title: irish scones
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and sift.
Add margarine and raisins.
Mix together well.
Add sour cream and a little milk. Knead into a round ball.
Cut into 16 pieces.
Bake in 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Grease a 9 inch pie plate or a 10 x 6 inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
(I sometimes add sausage I have browned and drained or ham I have cut into small pieces.)

title: corn flake candy
directions: Heat sugar and Karo syrup.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Let melt.
Pour over corn flakes and mix well.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.
Then cut into squares.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots and salt until tender.
Drain.
Blend other ingredients; beat well.
Alternate layers of carrots, onion and green pepper.
Pour sauce over carrots.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Blend well in blender; store in refrigerator.
For dip, decrease liquid.

title: lovely lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate lightly with Pam.
Sprinkle sides and bottom with graham cracker crumbs.
Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour into blender container.
Add cottage cheese and cream cheese product; cover.
Blend at medium speed, scraping down sides occasionally, about 2 minutes or until mixture is completely smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared pan; smooth top.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.
Remove side of pan.
Top cheesecake with pie filling.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook flour, sugar, boiling water and butter together until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and pour into baked pie shell.

title: carrots oregano
directions: Peel and quarter carrots.
Place in shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Add salt, water, butter and oregano.
Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: honey almond granola
directions: Heat oats in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Combine oats, sugar, wheat germ, coconut and almonds.
Stir until well mixed.
Add oil, honey and vanilla to dry mixture and stir well.
Now, bake in pan, stirring every few minutes, until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan. Serve as a cereal, topping for pudding or ice cream.
Store in a tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: spanish rice
directions: Crumble bacon and place that and drippings in skillet.
Add rice, onions and green pepper.
Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Quickly bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Yields 4 servings (good with cornbread).

title: denise's red hot jello salad
directions: Dissolve red hots and jello in water.
Mix in pineapple.
Allow to set.

title: nebraska butterscotch crunches
directions: Melt butterscotch over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand for 20 minutes before serving.
If desired, substitute 1 package of semi-sweet chocolate chips and one butterscotch.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large heavy saucepan, lightly brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: *Add enough water to the Ro-Tel to make 4 cups liquid.

title: pam's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa in small bowl until well blended. Melt butter in iron skillet. Add dry ingredients in butter and mix. Beat egg yolk until lemon-colored. Add milk to eggs and beat together. Add egg mixture to ingredients in skillet gradually while stirring constantly. Cool slowly. Add vanilla. Pour into cooled pie shell.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook 7 minutes, forming stiff peaks.
Add vanilla.
Use mixer to beat until glossy.
Do not use aluminum pans with this recipe.
It will turn gray.

title: e-z polenta bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Place all ingredients into mixing bowl and blend.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. (May also be baked in muffin tins.)

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring
to
a boil the jello, sugar and water; set aside to cool.
After
cooling, beat in cheese, pineapple, nuts and apricots
(baby
food).
Fold in Cool Whip until well blended. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 3 or 4 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: hot mustard
directions: Grind and drain peppers.
Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Boil 20 minutes.
Make a paste with 3/4 cup flour and the juice from the peppers.
Add to the hot pepper mixture.
Stir until thick.
Pour into pint jars and seal.
Yields 4 pints.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 8 muffin cups.
Beat eggs slightly. Beat in flour, milk and salt just until smooth.
Fill cups halfway.
Bake for 20 minutes at 450° and then decrease oven temperature to 350° for 15 minutes.
Immediately remove from cups and serve.

title: irish stew
directions: In the bottom of a heavy pan, layer the potatoes, meat and onion.
Begin with the potatoes.
Repeat this layering twice, ending with the potatoes on top.
Season with salt and pepper. Add the bay leaf; cover the mixture with water and parsley.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer over low heat for about 2 1/2 hours. Shake the pot periodically so that the potatoes do not stick. When done, the moisture should be absorbed by the potatoes.

title: onion pie
directions: Slice onions and allow to stand in water, salted with 1 teaspoon salt for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Place in shell and add flour and cream.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: harvard beets
directions: Bring beet juice and water to a boil.
In small pan, soften gelatin in vinegar.
Stir mixture in hot beet juice until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetener and milk.
Stir.
Add beets.
Refrigerate.
Serve.
If you like it hot, you may want to reheat.
Remember, if you boil milk, it curdles.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: In a
quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients. Bake, uncovered, at
for
about
1	hour or until heated through. Stir before serving.

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Stir together the egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Quickly stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Add walnuts.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook 1 minute.
Put 1/2 of meat mixture in baking dish, then chicken or mushroom soup.
Next, put remaining meat mixture, then Cheddar cheese soup.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and cover with Tater Tots.
I sometimes put grated cheese on top of Tater Tots also.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Lightly crush chips
and place in bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour
picante sauce and chicken broth over chips and stir gently
with
a
fork.
Spread chicken over the chips and season with
salt,
garlic
powder
and cumin.
In a small bowl combine soup
and
sour
cream.
Spoon over chicken.
Top with thinly sliced
Jack cheese and bake at 350° until browned on top and bubbly around the edges.

title: pineapple salad(good with ham)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix together pineapple, sugar, flour and 3 teaspoons juice.
Add cheese.
Spray a baking dish with Pam and pour in pineapple mixture.
Melt butter and add to crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top of pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Slice apples; put cinnamon and sugar on top and let sit. Cream sugar and oil; add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Alternate the orange juice and vanilla with dry ingredients.
Put batter on bottom, then layer of apples.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients into large Corning Ware bowl. Microwave for 7 minutes in a 900 or 1000 watts microwave.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave 2 more minutes.
Add baking soda stirring very fast until light and foamy.
Pour into greased pan. Let cool 30 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: mexican potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes.
Mix potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onion together.
Fry bacon and sprinkle on top of potato mixture in a pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn clam chowder
directions: If using fresh corn, remove corn from cobs.
Set aside.
Saute bacon in large pot until brown.
Remove bacon with slotted soup spoon and set aside.
Add celery and onions and cook in bacon fat until almost tender.
Pour in champagne and continue cooking until vegetables absorb liquid.
Return diced bacon to pot and stir in corn.
Moisten with cream.
Add thyme and simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Add clams to soup and continue cooking at a simmer until ready to serve.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: pollo aquascalientes
directions: Cook chicken in olive oil in a deep heavy pot, cast-iron is best, 15 to 20 minutes, turning.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over chicken.
Cover; turn down heat to a strong simmer.
Cook another 45 to 60 minutes until chicken is very tender.
Serve chicken on the side, with broth in a bowl.
Sprinkle broth with basil or serve together in a large soup bowl.
Sprinkle with basil.

title: brown sugar pork chops
directions: Season salt pork chops on both sides.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and shake the brown sugar and coat the tops real good.
Cover and cook at 325° for about an hour or until tender.

title: beef boogie woogie("crock-pot")
directions: Whisk mushroom soup, wine, soup mix and thyme in slow cooker until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and stir until everything is coated. Cover and cook on high 4 hours or on low 8 to 10 hours (until meat is very tender). Sprinkle with parsley.

title: diet cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and Sugar Twin.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Add 1 cup nuts, 1/2 cup raisins, 1/2 cup cherries and 1/2 cup coconut.
Spoon on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: shrimp-stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts.
Turn inside part of chicken breasts facing up.
Combine shrimp, celery and onion.
Place 1/2 shrimp mixture in small bowl with 1/2 cup soup.
Spread on chicken breasts, roll up and secure with toothpicks.
In 8-inch baking dish, melt butter in oven at 350°.
Place stuffed chicken in butter, rolling to coat all sides.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain off excess liquid.
In small bowl, combine remaining shrimp mixture with remaining soup.
Spoon over chicken in dish.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Remove toothpicks.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Stir sauce in pan.
Spoon over chicken breasts.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Combine bread, onion and seasonings.
Add butter and enough liquid to moisten.
Toss gently to mix.
Makes 4 cups stuffing, enough for a 4 or 5-pound chicken.
Double recipe for 10-pound turkey.

title: fit for heaven
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 2 eggs together; spread in a high-lipped cookie sheet.

title: roll-ups with cream cheese filling and feta cheese
directions: Mix cheeses and egg yolks to creamy paste.
Cut edges evenly from bread.
Press bread square down with rolling pin.
Brush slice of bread with butter that has been melted.
Drop a teaspoon of mix and roll into wheels.
Cut wheels in half and coat with egg whites and then in sesame seed.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: kugeli
directions: Saute the bacon with the onion. Drain and crumble. Add with other ingredients and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: walnut oatmeal chews
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Drop and press flat with fork.
Bake 10-12 minutes at 375°.
Note: Good with chocolate chips added; too.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In a large pot, saute onion, celery and potatoes in butter over low heat until onion is softened.
Add remaining ingredients, except fish.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add fish and simmer for 15 minutes more.
Be sure to remove bay leaf before serving.
Yield:
About 2 quarts or 8 to 12 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir until well blended.
Add 1 cup of coarsely chopped nuts (walnuts, etc.).
Pour into pans.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool on rack.
Makes two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaves.

title: jeb's favorite pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Brown pork chops on each side in a skillet.
Set aside.
Pour soup and water into skillet and mix with the pan drippings.
Pour liquids over the rice and place pork chops on top.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: my mom's and my aunt's tranquil tea
directions: Crush leaves and mix together.
Keep in tightly closed container in cool dark place.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at
325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched and pulls away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake!
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.
Serve warm or cool, with whipped topping, if desired.

title: cheese and wiener crescents
directions: Cut cheese slices into 6 strips each.
Slit hot dogs to within 1/2 inch of ends.
Insert 3 cheese strips in each hot dog.
Center hot dog on 1 crescent roll each and roll up.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown
hamburger, onion, celery and green peppers.
Add ketchup and seasoning;
simmer 20 minutes.

title: pudding icing
directions: Beat for 1 minute the milk, pudding and powdered sugar.
Then stir in 8 ounces Cool Whip.

title: coconut pie
directions: Filling:
Beat egg yolks.
Add to milk, cornstarch, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut.

title: marian's party cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to reach room temperature.
Combine in large mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Add Worcestershire sauce, spices and half the chopped nuts.
Chill.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Chill thoroughly.
Can be made ahead of time and frozen.
Serve with a heavy cracker.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Combine oleo, cocoa, oil and water in pan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar while hot.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake 20 minutes on cookie sheet at 375°.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all as for salad.
Pack in loaf pan.
Refrigerate and slice to serve.

title: brazil nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of 2 round layer pans (8 x 1 1/2-inch) with aluminum foil.
Beat egg whites in a large mixing bowl until foamy.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Beat egg yolks, oil and brandy in a small bowl at a low speed until blended.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, 1 teaspoon instant coffee, cinnamon and cloves; beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Fold egg yolk mixture into the egg whites.
Fold in cracker crumbs and 1 cup of nuts.
Pour this mixture into the prepared pans.
Bake until top springs back when touched lightly, approximately 30 to 35 minutes. Immediately invert the pans, resting rims on edges of 2 inverted pans.
Cool completely.
Loosen edges of layers with knife; invert pans and hit sharply on table.
Remove foil.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Marinate first 5 ingredients overnight.
Next morning, add the remaining items.
Mix and let stand several hours.
Keeps for several days in the refrigerator in a covered container.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat egg until smooth; add milk and melted shortening.
Pour this into the flour and sugar and mix a very soft dough.
Drop by spoonfuls into chicken, turkey or beef broth.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Mix chicken and soups together.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with Stove Top stuffing using directions on box.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook the raisins in the water.
Cool and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Combine the remaining ingredients; spread this mixture over top of pie.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn flake pudding
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour into a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Tastes like Indian Pudding.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Cook Stove Top stuffing as directed on box.
Add oleo and cool.
When cool, add soup, tuna and eggs; mix well.
Make into cakes and brown in oil or oleo of your choice.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Layer chicken, onions and pepper.
Dip tortilla in chicken broth.
Place on top.
Repeat layers in casserole dish.
Mix both soups together with Ro-Tel tomatoes and pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and sprinkle chili powder over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add chili powder, cumin, garlic powder and chili powder.
Add flour and taco sauce.
Add soups and heat. Tear tortillas into pieces.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Melt butter, adding sugar.
Add vanilla; bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add nuts.
Put graham crackers on two cookie sheets.
Spread mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: confetti coleslaw(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In bowl, combine cabbage, tomato, pepper and onions.
In small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend margarine, powdered sugar and 2 cups flour; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat the eggs until fluffy.
Add the sugar; beat at medium speed.
Add lemon juice and lemon rind.
Fold in the 4 tablespoons flour and the baking powder.
Spread over bottom layer; bake for 25 minutes. Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: low-fat quick mexican skillet
directions: Brown vegetables in nonstick Pam sprayed large skillet until onions are tender (approximately 5 minutes).
Add turkey and cook until pink is gone.
Add seasonings.
Mix tomatoes, water and rice.
Cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes on low simmer.
Stir occasionally until rice is done.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
This makes a big skillet.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: In large bowl, fold mayonnaise into yogurt and fold in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Blend eggs and sugar; add butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: warm crab and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl with electric mixer until smooth.
Add mayonnaise; beat until just blended.
Season with salt and pepper.
Using rubber spatula, fold in crabmeat, 1/4 cup Parmesan, artichoke hearts, green onion, celery, parsley, vinegar, and hot pepper sauce.
Transfer crab mixture to 2-cup souffle dish.
Top with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake until crab mixture is warm and cheese melts, about 15 minutes.
Transfer to platter.
Surround with toasts; serve immediately.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Note:
Use golden yellow Delicious apples for best results.

title: mini-blinis(makes 4 dozen; recipe may be cut in half)
directions: Combine yolks, cheese and sugar.
Roll bread thin (remove crusts).
Put 1 tablespoon filling in the center of each slice of bread.
Melt butter.
Make mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Dip in butter, then in cinnamon/sugar.
Drain on paper towels.
Bake until crispy (lightly toasted) and warm.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Beat together and spread in 13 x 9-inch greased dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add well-beaten egg yolks. Add mashed potatoes, then add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Beat egg whites until very stiff and fold into mixture carefully.
Pour into three (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix additional ingredients together in blender.
Stir altogether in large skillet and simmer 1 hour.

title: italian sausage lasagne
directions: Cook and stir sausage, onion and garlic in 10-inch skillet until sausage is brown; drain.
Stir in 2 tablespoons parsley, sugar, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Break up tomatoes. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until slightly thickened, about 45 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Mix Ricotta cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan, 1 tablespoon parsley and the oregano.
Spread 1 cup of sauce mixture in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Top with 4 noodles.
Spread 1 cup of cheese mixture over noodles; spread with 1 cup sauce.
Sprinkle with 2/3 cup Mozzarella.
Repeat with 4 noodles, the remaining cheese, 1 cup sauce and 2/3 cup Mozzarella.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 45 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp piquante
directions: Rinse scallops and dry with a paper towel.
Roll scallops in flour.
In a wok or large skillet, saute scallops and garlic in olive oil until tender (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Add snow peas, red peppers and mushrooms and mix until heated through.
Serve over rice.
Serves 5.
Per serving: 214 total calories and 13 saturated fat calories.

title: peking pot roast
directions: Cut slits all over the roast.
Insert slices of garlic and onion in slits.
Put beef in bowl and pour vinegar over it, making sure it runs into the slits.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Discard vinegar when ready to cook.
Place meat in heavy pot and brown in oil until almost burned on all sides.
Pour coffee over roast. Add water and cover.
Cook this slowly at a simmer for 6 hours on top of stove.
Twenty minutes before removing from stove, add salt and pepper.
Meat will fall apart.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shells.
Top with nuts.
Put in freezer overnight or 3 hours before serving.
Take out 30 minutes before serving.

title: crunchy lemon chicken
directions: Mix cereal, lemon peel and salt; dip chicken pieces into egg white and then coat with cereal mixture.
Place on a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.
Real good!

title: caldo gallego(a hearty soup from northwest spain)
directions: In a large pot, combine first 9 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer on low about 3 hours or until beans are tender.
When meat is tender, take out so that it won't overcook. Add the potatoes and broccoli rabe.
Taste broth; add salt if needed.
Cook for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Cut meat into bite size pieces and return to pot.
Serve in large soup bowls.
Include pieces of meat, potato, beans and greens in each portion.

title: strawberry crepes
directions: Grease a 6 or 7-inch skillet lightly and heat until hot.
Beat baking mix, milk and eggs with hand beater until smooth.
For each crepe, pour 2 tablespoons batter into skillet.
Rotate skillet until batter covers the bottom.
Cook until golden brown.
Gently loosen edge with metal spatula.
Turn and cook on other side until golden brown.
Stack crepes placing waxed paper between each. Keep covered to keep from drying.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in saucepan (or double boiler over water) over low heat.
Then stir in peanuts and shoestring potatoes until mixed well.
Then spoon out by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: elegant krispie bars
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter in a 2-quart bowl and microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes until melted; stir twice. Add cereal and peanuts.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: el hallmark cheese dip
directions: Chop Velveeta into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients into microwave bowl.
Cook in microwave until cheese melts.
Stir frequently, adding milk if necessary to reach proper consistency.

title: halushkie russian noodles and cabbage
directions: Grate cabbage and onion fine.
Melt butter in pan, adding grated cabbage and onion, salt and pepper.
Saute until onion and cabbage are soft and brown.
Boil noodles until tender; drain.
Add cabbage and onion mixture.
Cube 1 stick butter over mixture.
Mix well.
Serve hot with side dish of cottage cheese.
This is even better the next day.

title: chewy raisin walnut shortbread bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease an 8 inch square pan. Combine flour and sugar using pastry blender or fork. Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine meal.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add next four ingredients and mix well.
Next, add squash and mix well, then add milk and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: waffles
directions: Put eggs, milk and shortening into blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Blend on low speed until almost smooth, stopping blender to scrape down sides, if necessary.
Yields 3 cups.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine peanut butter, softened butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat until creamy. Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into peanut butter mixture. Spread into greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle 1 (12 ounce) package semi-sweet Nestles chocolate over surface.
Place in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; run knife through to marbleize.
Return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: potato puff casserole
directions: Beat mashed potatoes, salt, pepper and egg yolks together. Add celery salt, cheese, onion and green pepper.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks; fold into potato mixture.
Spoon lightly into a greased 7 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate nut bars
directions: Melt the caramels with 1/3 of the milk on low until smooth. Mix rest of the milk with cake mix and margarine.
Press 1/2 of the batter in bottom of ungreased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over batter and top with melted caramels.
Cover with pecans and coconut.
Put remaining batter on top.
Cook 18 to 10 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix the brown sugar, white sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla together.
In separate bowl, mix the flour, oatmeal, soda, corn flakes and salt.
Combine both mixtures in a very large bowl. Roll into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli; drain and save liquid.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cream of chicken soup, Cheez Whiz and Minute rice. Add enough water to broccoli liquid to make 1 cup.
Add to mixture; stir in drained broccoli.
Pour into greased dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill.
To serve as an appetizer, pour Jezebel Sauce over the cream cheese and serve with crackers.
Sauce also good served with turkey or ham.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, add Mozzarella cheese.

title: buffet cheese-scalloped carrots
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Cook carrots as usual in water. Drain.

title: double peanut cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 or 9 minutes (chocolate chips may be added).

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the cake mix, eggs, water and butter together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour two cups of cake mix in pan.
Cook for 15 minutes or until done.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool
whip,
lemon	juice and Eagle Brand milk; add nuts, pineapple and cherries.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Makes 2 pies.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until liquid begins to cook away at 350°.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg yolks one at a time and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together three times.
Add alternately with sour cream and water.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 3 (9-inch) layers about 25 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: phyllo-spinach pie
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter and cook onions until it turns clear, about 5 minutes.
Add spinach and stir to mix.
Remove from heat and reserve.
Using a large bowl, beat eggs and stir in cheese, parsley, dill, salt, pepper and the spinach mixture.
Mix well. Brush a 13 x 9-inch pan with clarified butter and layer a phyllo sheet, brushing it on top with butter.
Build a foundation of 8 such butter lined layers.
Line the foundation with the spinach and egg mixture, spreading evenly.
Top with
8 more layers of buttered phyllo.
Using scissors, trim edges of dough that are overlapping the pan. Press down gently and pour remaining butter over the top.
Cut pie into narrow rectangles before baking.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool slightly, but serve warm.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine first four items.
Blend well.
Stir in applesauce. Mix well.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Put hole through top of ornament using a straw.
Pick up shape with spatula.
Put on cookie sheet. Let dry uncovered 4 to 5 days.
Put ribbon through hole.
Store in Ziploc bags when not in use.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in pineapple.
Measure flour by dipping or sifting.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend in nuts and coconut.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: sue's vegetable-beef soup
directions: Boil beef and save the broth to cook ingredients in.
Add beef broth and cubes; boil beef until tender.
Add ingredients.
Add tomatoes last.
Cook in large kettle or large roaster.
Very tasty and good for you!

title: something good
directions: 1st Layer:
Press flour, nuts and melted oleo into bottom of an 8 x 11 x 2-inch oven dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325° and let cool completely.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until it will spin a thread.
Pour 1/2 of syrup over beaten egg whites.
Cook other half until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat; pour onto greased plate to cool.
Cut in squares.
Peanut butter or nuts can be added, if desired.

title: fabulous swordfish kabobs
directions: Soak bay leaves in water for 1 hour.
Place fish in large plastic bag inside bowl.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Chop onion; saute in 1/2 stick of margarine until tender.
Add soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Melt the remaining margarine and add to the dressing crumbs.
Put 1/2 of the dressing in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Mix all squash ingredients together.
Pour on dressing.
Spread remaining half of the dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add onion and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: penne primavera with smoked mozzarella
directions: In large saucepan add 2 tablespoons oil and cook shallot and 1/2 garlic one minute.
Stir in tomatoes, basil, oregano and salt. Break up tomatoes with fork.
Simmer and cook partially covered 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: shirley's shrimp curry
directions: Saute shrimp in butter 3 to 5 minutes over low heat.
Saute garlic, stirring often, for 1 minute.
Add soups and stir until blended.
Stir in sour cream and curry powder.
Cook and stir until piping hot.
Serve immediately with rice.
Garlic bread goes great with this.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Combine 1/2 cup scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm with cold water.
Add yeast and mix well.
Blend in egg.
Add flour until dough is blended and soft.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Store in refrigerator at least 2 hours or until needed.
Shape into 18 rolls.
Let rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix well margarine, sugar and peanut butter.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
With a toothpick, dip balls in chocolate.
Set on wax paper until chocolate sets.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 104 pieces.

title: lime pie
directions: Thaw limeade.
Mix with electric mixer; add other ingredients. Add a couple of drops food coloring.
Pour in standard graham cracker crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: special chicken
directions: Wrap bacon around each breast.
Place breasts on bed of dried beef in greased baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake 2 hours at 250°.
The last 15 minutes, sprinkle with a little paprika. Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Can also put a jar of mushrooms in optionally.

title: chocolate-chess-pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: lucky if you get a bite
directions: First Layer:
butter, pecans and plain flour.
Bake the crust for 15 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: kelly's chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in pan with 1/2 stick butter and some of the broth from chicken. Cook until tender. Add can full of broth. Add rest of ingredients in baking pan.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: red lobster biscuits or cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix together for 30 seconds.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
Remove from oven and brush on 1/4 cup melted oleo, 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder and some dill weed.

title: pralines #2
directions: Boil and stir 10 minutes.
Test for soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Remove from heat.
Stir until thick.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold in pumpkin mixture and pour and spread into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup finely chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Take out of pan and put on towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up cake in towel and let cool.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients, and mix well. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add to the potato chip mixture and mix well. Stir in the pecans. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet, allowing space for the cookies to spread. Bake at 375 degrees for 10-15 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 5 dozen.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Arrange drained pineapple in baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour together and sprinkle over pineapple.
Then, sprinkle cheddar cheese over this.
Melt margarine and then break up Ritz Crackers in small pieces and mix in with margarine.
Cover top with rest of mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: diabetic-fruit medley salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, soften gelatin in orange juice.
Stir in boiling water, salt and liquid sweetener.
Chill until slightly thickened, but not set.
Carefully stir in fruit.
Pour into 3 or 4-cup mold or 6 individual molds.
Chill until set, about 4 hours. Serves 6.

title: froot loop cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Add Froot Loops and peanuts.
Drop by
teaspoon
on waxed paper.
When cool, store in tightly sealed container.

title: renee's pastry wrapped gouda
directions: Cut cheese in half to form two circles.
Divide can of rolls in half.
Set one half aside.
Lay the 2 rectangles next to each other on a baking sheet.
Pinch perforations to seal.
Place 1/2 cheese in center.
Spread with 1 1/2 teaspoons mustard.
Fold in corners and pinch edges shut.
Brush with beaten egg.
Repeat with other half of dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy chicken spinach casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Defrost spinach, cook as directed on package.
Squeeze dry. Spread spinach in greased casserole dish.

title: buckeye-reese's cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll into balls the size of walnuts; refrigerate.
Next day, dip in mixture of chocolate chips and paraffin, melted.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and juice, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Mix well.
Put half of mixture in an 11 x 5-inch pan and let congeal.
Spread sour cream on top.
Gently add rest of Jell-O mixture on top and let congeal overnight.

title: vee's souper spaghetti
directions: Brown beef with onion, mushrooms and pepper.
Stir in soups, one at a time, until smooth.
Add drained spaghetti.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until tender (10 to 15 minutes); drain.
Butter up large baking dish and dump in noodles.
Drain tuna fish and peas and add to noodles.
Add oleo and soup and mix well.
Add salt, pepper and milk and mix well.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: summer sauce
directions: Cut tomatoes into chunks.
Add finely minced garlic, basil, salt, pepper and olive oil.
Marinate at room temperature about 2 hours.
Cook pasta.
While cooking, add Mozzarella to tomatoes. Drain pasta.
Top with tomato mixture.
Serve.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine sugar and cider.
Tie spices in bag; slowly boil. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot with cinnamon sticks.

title: parslied rice
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add rice, stirring well.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups of sifted flour and 1/2 cup of milk alternately. Beat in eggs one at a
time.
Add the rest of the flour and milk alternately.
Add flavorings and salt.
Pour in large greased and floured tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Turn on 325°.
Cook for 1 hour.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 15 minutes; do not open the door.
Cool on rack 15 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice the cucumbers and onions thin.
Mix the salt into them and let stand
3 hours.
Combine sugar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed, vinegar
and
water.
Add
to cucumbers and onions. Heat; put in jars and seal.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add onion to meat.
Place meat in tortillas.
Roll and place in pan.

title: linguini summer salad - cold
directions: Cook linguini and drain.
While hot add the salad dressing and Salad Supreme spice.
Mix well.
Cool.
Add cucumbers and tomatoes.
Serve cold.

title: vidalia onion recipe
directions: Slice onions in rings and saute in skillet or microwave in butter until clear but still firm.
Layer in casserole, starting with onions, then crackers and cheese.
End layers with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine eggs, butter, apple butter and milk in large bowl.
Beat well.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in medium size bowl.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir just to moisten.
Pour batter into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on rack.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: sloppy joes, updated
directions: Put oil in a nonstick frypan over medium heat.
Add scallions, green pepper and carrots.
Heat until tender.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add tomatoes, orange juice, steak sauce and raisins.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve open-faced on whole wheat buns.

title: heavenly fruit dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add Jell-O to this mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add strawberries to Jell-O mixture.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until gelled.
You may use any fruit and any flavor of Jell-O.

title: water chestnut casserole
directions: Cook celery for 6 minutes and drain.
Combine soup, celery and water chestnuts in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Saute cracker crumbs in butter and spread over mixture.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and celery; cook until clear.
Arrange fowl in layer over this, then add noodles.
Mix salt, pepper, broth and chicken soup.
Pour over noodles, being careful to moisten all of the noodles.
Place mushrooms over top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Cover and cook in electric skillet at 360°, until steaming, then turn back to 220° for 30 minutes.
(On stove, start on high; turn back to low.) Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: grilled chicken livers
directions: You will need 12 (8 x 8-inch) squares of aluminum foil.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together cake mix (reserve 1 cup for topping), 1 stick oleo (melted) and 1 egg.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the pumpkin pie mix, 2 eggs and Pet milk.
Pour over cake mixture. Mix 1 cup of the cake mix, 1/4 cup oleo, sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in glass pan; 10 minutes longer in metal pan.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: sausage balls
directions: In a mixing bowl, put in sausage.
Add cheese gradually.
Add Bisquick and work with hands until thoroughly mixed.
Squeeze cheese and sausage as you would in making dough biscuits.
Roll out in balls.
Cook at 450° about 6 minutes.
May refrigerate after cooling.
Warms up well in oven or microwave.

title: depression era meat loaf
directions: Mix ground meat, 1/2 cup ketchup, egg, onion or minced onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt well by hand and add corn flakes. Mix again and form loaf; put in roaster pan.
Cover with 1/3 cup ketchup and bacon strips.
Add water to pan.
(I put in potatoes and carrots.)
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients togerher.
Pour half batter in hot greased pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over batter.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until done, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lone star lemon bars
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: yeast bread
directions: In large bowl mix yeast in very little warm water and set aside.
Mix all ingredients together; smooth dough and put oil on top to smooth.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour or longer.
Turn out onto floured board; roll dough and make rolls.
Butter and let rise about 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Add chopped onions and celery.
Let cook for awhile.
Add carrots which have been diced.
Add tomato sauce and rice.
Let simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve on browned buns.

title: quiche for one
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, beat egg and milk. Beat in margarine, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into an individual small baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 30 minutes, until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and cube.
Mix mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, Old Bay, lemon, mustard, Accent, eggs, onion, pepper, carrots and butter.
Butter casserole (approximately 9 x 12-inch).
Mix crumbs and seafood.
Add enough sauce to make mixture pasty.
Pat a little sauce on bottom of pan. Put crabmeat mixture in pan.
Cover with remaining sauce and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer pepper, tomatoes, onions, rice and pork chops in large baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour sherry over layers and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 3 to 5.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice
thin.
Combine
sugar and flour, spices and salt.
Mix
with
apples.
Fill pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate and dot
with
butter.
Adjust
top crust.	Sprinkle with sugar. Bake in 400° oven
for 50 minutes or until juices bubble through the top.

title: no mess lasagna
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups of spaghetti sauce into a 9 x 12-inch lasagna pan.
Add a layer of raw noodles.
Add 1/2 of the meat in small chunks.
Sprinkle with onion and spoon on the cottage cheese. Cover with 1 1/2 cups of sauce, then a layer of noodles.
Layer the sliced American cheese and rest of meat in small pieces.
Pour on 2 cups sauce.
Press down.
Pour hot water gently over top.
Press down again.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove foil.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered another 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: saucy sausage-stuffed squash
directions: Scoop flesh from squash, leaving 1/4-inch thick shell. Dice flesh. Cook sausage and diced squash in a large nonstick skillet, breaking up sausage with a spoon, 5 minutes or until browned and cooked. Remove to a bowl; stir in tomatoes. Put squash halves cut side down in skillet. Add 2 tablespoons of water. Cover and cook 2 minutes. Turn squash over. Cover and cook 2 minutes. Fill with sausage mixture. Cover; cook over low heat 2 minutes to reheat. Serves 4.

title: cookie crumb crust
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl.
Pack in a pie pan.
It is now ready to fill.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, cucumber, pepper and onion.
Combine garlic, basil and remaining ingredients with a wire whisk until blended. Pour over tomato mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Yields 5 servings - 1 cup per serving.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; taste for seasoning.
A little extra vinegar or lemon juice and a pinch of salt may be required, depending on kind of mayonnaise used.
Serve with any fish or seafood.
Yield: about 2 cups.

title: miniature reese's cups
directions: Combine powdered sugar, butter and peanut butter. Roll into balls; chill. Dip in melted chocolate. Cool, eat and enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together butter and cheese; pour over drained broccoli in greased casserole.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Melt another stick of butter (whole) and pour over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix butter with crumbs and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn topped meat loaf
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and 1/2 cup corn lightly, but thoroughly.
Pack in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in preheated 400° oven, about 45 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes, then turn out on hot platter.
Heat remaining corn and pour over top of loaf.
If desired, garnish with pimiento strips and parsley. Serves 6.

title: oven stew
directions: Place ingredients in layers in casserole dish or Dutch oven. Don't mix and don't brown meat.
Bake in 250° oven for 4 to 5 hours, covered.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat sweet potatoes, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, 1/4 cup butter, eggs, vanilla and granulated sugar until smooth.
Pour into buttered 2-quart souffle dish.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup butter, brown sugar, flour and pecans.
Sprinkle on top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Combine with taco seasoning and refried beans and spread in a baking dish.
Combine sour cream and taco sauce and spread on top of beef/bean mixture.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly (approximately 30 minutes).
Serve with taco chips.

title: yakitori
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch size cubes.
Boil shoyu, Mirin, sugar and
chicken bones in a
saucepan.	Simmer,
uncovered, until mixture is reduced by 1/4.	Cool.
Dip chicken in sauce. Thread skewer with chicken, mushrooms and	green
onions.	Dip in sauce; grill on barbecue.

title: baked cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Mix until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.

title: ez chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken, Veg All, and gravy in pie plate and cover with pie crust. Crimp edges.
Poke holes in crust to release steam. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place partially thawed broccoli in a greased baking dish. Melt butter and use half over the broccoli.
Crumb the crackers and mix with the remaining butter.
Top broccoli with cubed cheese.
Spread cracker crumb mixture over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shells.
Don't shake middle.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 5 pies.

title: kyle's favorite stew
directions: In large stock pot, lightly brown beef in cooking oil.
Add several cups of water and bring to a boil.
Stir in dry soup mix, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and carrots and enough water to cover vegetables.
Reduce heat and continue cooking for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta fagioli(macaroni and beans)
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in oil until soft but not browned. Add tomato sauce and simmer for about 1 hour.
Drain beans, reserving one cup of liquid for sauce.
Add the liquid to the sauce and continue cooking, stirring constantly until the sauce becomes thick and smooth.
Add drained beans, sugar, salt, pepper and oregano or Italian seasoning and cook 15 minutes longer.
Cook the macaroni about 10 minutes or according to package directions. Do not overcook.
Drain very well in a colander until it is completely liquid free and add it to the beans and sauce.
Heat for about 5 minutes until it is very hot.
Use lots of grated Romano cheese when served and a loaf of Italian bread.
Serves 4.

title: candied yams
directions: Drain off and discard water from 1 can sweet potatoes.
Put both cans of potatoes and liquid in an ovenproof dish.
Add sugar, cinnamon, butter and nutmeg.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven.
Turn oven temperature to broil; put marshmallows on potatoes and return to oven for 30 seconds or until marshmallows are browned.
Remove from oven to cool.
Makes 5 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: best western barbecue bean bake
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: hungry boy's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown beef.
Stir in celery, bell peppers and onions and cook until glazed.
Drain off excess grease. Stir in pork and beans, catsup, water, salt and garlic salt until well blended.
Pour into a casserole, reserving 1/2 cup of bean-meat mixture.
Place casserole in oven for 10 minutes while preparing the biscuits.
Arrange biscuits, without centers, on the casserole.
Spoon reserved bean-meat filling in the center holes of each biscuit.
Put biscuit holes over the top of the casserole. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, until the biscuits are golden brown.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Sprinkle chopped nuts evenly over crumbs.
Scatter chocolate morsels over nuts.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over chocolate morsels.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over coconut.

title: apple dandy sandwiches(for 6 open-faced sandwiches)
directions: For each sandwich, spread toast with margarine; cover with slice of cheese and 3 apple rings rolled in brown sugar.
Broil until cheese begins to melt.
Top with 2 bacon slices.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Beat butter until fluffy.
Add food coloring and mix well. Add remaining ingredients; mixing well.
Shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate peanut butter ice cream
directions: You take 2 pieces of bread and then you take on piece of cheese.
Put the piece of cheese in the middle.
Then you put it in a pan and bake it for 8 minutes.
Then you cut it into 4 pieces.
That's it!

title: spinach cheese appetizer
directions: Melt butter on a cookie sheet.
This greases the pan and blends into other ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese and spinach; mix well.
