Spread onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
May be frozen.
To reheat, bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: texas crackers
directions: Put crackers in a sealed container. Mix all ingredients and pour over crackers. Marinate overnight. Shake container or stir with spoon several times.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in a loaf in a baking pan. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until well done.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar and press into a 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid as usual.
Add cranapple juice.

title: tofu special k meat loaf
directions: Blend tofu until smooth in blender or food processor.
Mix all ingredients together in a very large bowl, adding cereal last. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, lightly sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and crispy (may take longer than regular Special K Meat Loaf).
There is very little difference in using tofu, surprisingly!
The main difference is the texture may be softer compared to the regular recipes crispness.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well with fingers.
Add to creamed potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add apples, then egg and milk.
Fold gently, just enough to blend. Bake in greased and floured muffin tins at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes 16 large muffins.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, oats, onion, beaten egg, salt, pepper and 1 can tomato sauce.
Form into loaf.
Put in a shallow 7 x 10-inch pan.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic until brown; drain.
Stir in sauce, mushrooms, sugar, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring, and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Mix Bisquick, milk and egg.
Spread half in pan.
Top with 4 slices of cheese.
Spoon beef over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese slices; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Drop remaining dough by spoonful onto cheese and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy tuna and noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
In a large saucepan, melt butter and cook onion until tender. Stir in flour and salt blended with milk.
Bring to the boiling point, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, peas, tuna, pimiento and noodles.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: summer pizza
directions: Press rolls onto cookie sheet.
Bake according to package directions; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch mix. Spread on baked crescent rolls.
Sprinkle vegetables on top. Refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: layer taco dip
directions: Add chili powder and picante sauce to refried beans.
Combine bean mixture with seasoning mix and 2 tablespoons sour cream and spread in a 13 x 9-inch serving dish.
Layer avocado dip, rest of sour cream, tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Place rhubarb in buttered casserole.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
In a bowl, blend remaining sugar, rolled oats, butter, flour and salt with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of rhubarb. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly saute onion, garlic and bell pepper until translucent.
Process canned tomatoes in food processor to eliminate chunks.
Place all ingredients except shrimp in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Add shrimp, pushing well down into the rice mixture.
Sprinkle with juice of 1/2 lemon. Re-cover and bake 1/2 hour longer or until rice is done.
Serves 4.
Double recipe for a 3-quart casserole.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients and pour over crackers.
Mix well until all crackers are moist.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: In a large bowl, blend flour, sugar, soda, salt and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix and roll out or can be cut in shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook until light brown or barely golden around edges, about 8 to 10 minutes, at 300°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.

title: rio grande tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles al dente according to package instructions.
Drain well.
In large bowl, mix noodles, soup, milk, chilies, taco sauce, tuna, salt, pepper and 2 cups cheese.
Spoon into shallow baking dish.
Cover with the crushed tortilla chips and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fettucini carbonara
directions: Cook bacon, drain and crumble; reserve 3 tablespoons of fat. Add cream and simmer; do not boil.
Cook fettucini; drain.
Add margarine and toss.
Add beaten eggs; toss.
Add cream and bacon fat; toss.
Add cheese and crumbled bacon; toss and serve immediately.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a small bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Add chicken. Marinate 15 minutes.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare wild rice according to package directions.
Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Remove from heat; stir in flour.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough broth to liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Gradually stir into flour mixture.
Add cream.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add rice, mushrooms, chicken, pimento, salt and pepper.
Place in 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 10.
(It takes about 1 1/2 fryers to make 3 cups diced chicken.)

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Grease a baking sheet lightly.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking.
Set to moderately hot, 415° to 425°.
Measure sugar and shortening and cream well.
Add egg and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in nutmeg, vanilla and salt.
Stir soda into buttermilk and add flour and buttermilk, a bit at a time.
Begin and end with flour.
Stir until smooth.
Remove 1/3 of dough at a time to floured cloth and roll out about 1/8-inch thick. (Sprinkle with sugar.)
Cut out and lift to pan with pancake turner.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes (just blonde, not brown).
Makes 36 Tea Cakes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter; add dry rice.
Braise well until butter begins to bubble.
Add broth and seasoning; mix well.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 400°.
Take out of oven; mix well and bake 15 minutes more.

title: granola carrot cake
directions: Microwave butter in a 2 1/2-quart glass mixing bowl at High 30 seconds.
Blend in brown sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in carrots, flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and granola cereal.
Grease the bottom only of an 8-inch round baking dish.
Pour batter into dish; microwave at High 7 to 8 minutes. Rotate dish at 3 minute intervals.
Cool thoroughly before frosting with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry yum-yums
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take frozen pie crust and press a few pecans into crust.
Mix with spoon 1/2 of Cool Whip, 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese in bowl until smooth (will be slightly lumpy). Pour into pie crusts.
Cover with layer of pie filling (your favorite), then top with the remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and Crisco. Blend until well creamed. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Add flour and milk alternately, then add flavoring. Bake 1 hour at 325°, then at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: kiperdies
directions: Cream butter.
Mix sugar and flour through sifter.
Gradually add to butter.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Form balls; press down with thumb or fork.
Bake at 250° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: jody's cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together. Cream shortening, white sugar and brown sugar together.
Stir in egg, vanilla, cereal and oatmeal.
Beat all together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.
Flatten with knife or fork dipped in cold water.
For delicate cookies, flatten until almost paper thin.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 60.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, salt and soda. Add 2 cups fruit cocktail plus the juice.
Beat 3 minutes with mixer.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup nuts and spread over cake batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Chill cookie dough until very firm.
Line 14 inch pizza pan with foil.
Slice cookie dough into 1/8 inch slices and line pizza pan with cookie slices beginning in center and working towards outside of pan.
Overlap edges until pan is covered.
Press cookie dough together by pressing with fingers.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and cool completely. Transfer cookie pizza to serving tray.

title: lamagna's cassata
directions: With serrated knife, slice crust off pound cake on all sides, then slice cake lengthwise into 1/4-inch slice, rectangular.

title: easy cheese enchiladas
directions: Saute onion.
Add ground beef and brown; drain.
Place some ground beef and cheese in a line in the center of a flour tortilla.
Roll and place seam side down in a baking dish.
Place rolled enchiladas side by side.
Pour sauce over.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 30 minutes at 350° (until bubbly).

title: candy
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and milk; cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in lightly buttered pan.

title: dip the shrimp
directions: Chop ingredients finely.
Mix well and enjoy.
Sprinkle the parsley on top.
Decorate side of bowl with shrimp.

title: strawberry bottom cheesecake
directions: Place sliced strawberries on paper towels to drain. Beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream & vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blend well.

Spread a thin layer of strawberry glaze over bottom of crust. Place strawberry slices on glaze & cover with another thin later of strawberry glaze. Then gently pour mixture over glazed berries in crust.
Cover & chill until set, at least 4 hours.

title: 7 - layer salad
directions: First Layer:
Slice a layer of lettuce.
Fill dish 1/2 full of lettuce.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover pie filling with crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Arrange margarine on top of cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl. Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; cookies will be soft.
Allow to cool on cookie sheet for 10 minutes before removing them to a plate or cooling rack.
Cookies will harden as they cool.

title: peanut butter pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in a large bowl the pumpkin, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in half and half, Southern Comfort, vanilla, nutmeg and salt.
Pour into prepared pie shell. Bake until uniformly puffed, at 425° for 20 minutes. Then reduce heat to 350° for 40 minutes.
Pie will fall slightly in center as it cools.
Can be prepared day ahead and refrigerated.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in a plastic bag or food processor.
(Crush 10 at a time and use for each of the 3 layers.)
Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
In another bowl, mix together milk, instant pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures. Alternate layers of mixture and cookie crumbs in a clean 6 1/2-inch flower pot.
Start and end with cookie crumbs.
Chill. Decorate with a stem of plastic flowers.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: smoked mullet spread
directions: Remove skin and bones from fish.
Flake fish well.
Combine all ingredients; mix well and chill at least 1 hour.
Makes approximately 3 cups spread.
Great with Wheat Thins.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add margarine and other ingredients. Knead on a floured board for 5 minutes.
Press or roll out to 1/2-inch thick or less and cut out with a biscuit cutter.
Let rise in a greased pan for 1 hour in a warm place.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for butter and flour in a pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend butter with flour with a wire whisk and add to corn.
Mix well and remove from heat. Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and put under broiler until lightly browned.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: In a bowl, put crushed garlic cloves, salt, paprika, pepper and tomatoes.
Mash ingredients thoroughly with a fork.
Add, drop by drop, the olive and vegetable oils.
Stir vigorously with a whisk.
Add onion, pepper, cucumber, bread crumbs, wine vinegar and water.
Stir and chill.
You may also add leftover, fresh cooked corn.

title: bea's old time biscuit pudding
directions: Mix and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: corn dogs
directions: Roll wieners.
Drain and dry off with paper towels.
Use popsicle sticks and stick into end of wieners.
Combine all other ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Roll wieners in batter. Hold wieners with fork into hot frying oil until brown.
Drain on paper towels to collect grease.

title: pumpkin cookie dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme until smooth.
Stir in pumpkin, cinnamon and orange peel.
Serve as a dip with cookies.
Store in the refrigerator. Yield: 4 cups.

title: alabama trash
directions: Melt butter and add pecans.
In a mixing bowl, sift sugar and add milk.
Mix well.
Add coconut.
Mix and add pecan mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper.
Cool in refrigerator at least one hour (preferably overnight, balls will be easier to handle).
Melt chocolate and wax in top of a double boiler.
Take 6 or 8 balls out of the refrigerator at the time. With a toothpick dip one ball at a time until covered.
Place on wax paper.
Makes approximately 60 balls.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheddar cheese
directions: Empty soup in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in milk gradually. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 20 to 35 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: *May use nonfat yogurt and sour cream.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns all day or overnight.
In a large bowl, mix margarine, sour cream and cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread corn flakes over mixture and dot generously with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: marinade for flank steak
directions: Marinate at least 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Barbecue or broil.
Slice at an angle for maximum tenderness.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to batter, little at a time.
Beat until well blended and creamy.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes back clear of batter.

title: souper-tuna noodle bake
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Stir.
Top with sliced cheese and croutons.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and flour; stir in coconut and nuts.
Press 3/4 of the mixture into a 15 x 10-inch ungreased pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
After 15 minutes, remove from oven and spread 18 ounces of apricot preserves over crust. Crumble remaining mixture over the preserves and bake for an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
I usually have to keep it in for 30 minutes.
These are super the next day.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in blender; blend at highest speed.
With blender on at high speed, slowly drizzle salad oil in a steady stream.
By end of adding oil, it should be thick and creamy.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 cup.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat.
Blend mayo, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Put pastry shell.
Bake at 350 for 35 - 40 mins. or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: icebox kolaches
directions: Dissolve yeast with part of the potato water.
Add sugar, salt and eggs; mix real well. Add milk and Wesson oil, mixing after each addition. Add the flour.
Mix well.
Put in the refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.
When you take the dough out of the refrigerator, roll dough in small ball sizes.
Let rise for 20 minutes. Brush with oleo.
Use your favorite filling. Bake at 375° until brown.
Remove from oven and brush with oleo.

title: easy brickle cake
directions: Combine pecans, coconut and 2 tablespoons melted butter. Spread in bottom of a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan. Set aside.

title: baked cod
directions: Place cod fillets in baking dish and brush with lemon juice and oil.
Cover with thin slices of onion rings.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover fish with slices of peeled orange and minced parsley.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes more or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Cook dumplings in broth and then add rest of ingredients to dumplings, including chicken. Pour in casserole dish and cover with bread crumbs.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Serves 18 to 20 people.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first five ingredients; stir.
In large bowl, beat shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
To this, add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in the oatmeal and raisins; drop from spoon onto buttered tin and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake(serves a large crowd)
directions: Spray 11 x 15-inch pan with cooking spray, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake cake and cool.

title: enchilada sauce or red chile for stew
directions: Cook bacon.
Take out cooked bacon and put flour and chili powder in hot grease on low heat for a few minutes.
Stir in 1 can of chicken broth and some water until gravy is boiling.
Pour in blended chili peppers, along with whole garlic clove.
Simmer for approximately 20 minutes.
Add salt, onion powder and garlic powder to taste.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese).
Mix well.
Put in lightly greased 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Cover top with chips or corn chips (crushed up).
Put back into oven and bake another 10 minutes.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken, reserving 3 cups of broth.
Remove meat from bones and cut up.
Add potatoes and carrots to broth and bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Add chicken, corn, tomato sauce and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: maple sweetheart pie
directions: Line sides of 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers. Sprinkle gelatin over water in small saucepan; let stand 1 minute. Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Bring maple syrup in heavy saucepan to a boil; continue boiling until it reaches 230° on a candy thermometer.

title: baked broccoli with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli and spread in a shallow casserole dish.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add flour, salt and milk, cooking until thickened.
Add cheeses and blend well.
Pour sauce over the broccoli; top with crumbs and bake 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked apple and carrot casserole
directions: Combine flour and sugar; sprinkle over apples and carrots layered in baking pan.
Pour orange juice over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry-cherry-pineapple salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce until hot.
Add cherry jello; stir until jello is dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Stir; put into mold and chill.

title: commercial precooked rice(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a deep 3-quart casserole.
Heat 25 minutes covered or until rice is tender.
Let stand 10 minutes. Pour rice in colander and rinse with hot water.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cranberry gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar and fresh cranberries.
Peel and grind orange and use juice.
Add to jello mix.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: mounds cake
directions: Cook cake as directed in 2 layers.
Let layers cool and split, making 4 layers.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and
onions
thin.
Fill
gallon jar or container that can	be
covered.
Layer
cucumbers	and onion. Mix cold the rest of the ingredients.
Stir well and pour over cucumber-onion slices.
Put
in refrigerator.
Shake jar every morning for 7 to
days	to
mix
spices and dissolve sugar well.
(If you do
not
have enough cucumbers to fill jar, add to mixture.)
After
mixture
has
"pickled"
(approximately 2 weeks) to suit your
taste,
this	may be put in smaller jars. They do not have
to be sealed.
Must be kept in refrigerator. They will keep for up to a year.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in greased casserole dish at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with sliced cheese when done and bake until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender and drain.
Cook onion and pepper in oleo until partially tender.
Mix all ingredients and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Add bread crumbs and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: swedish cream(serves 4)
directions: Heat cream, sugar and gelatin.
Add sour cream and vanilla. Mix.
Pour into bowl or mold.
Chill.
Serve with fresh or thawed berries, raspberries, strawberries or blackberries.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, walnuts, baking powder, baking soda, apple pie spice and salt.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly. Stir in honey, salad oil, zucchini and vanilla. Stir liquid mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Spread equally into loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans. Makes 2 loaves.

title: fall potato soup
directions: Steam potatoes until very tender.
Peel and cut into bite size pieces when cool.
Saute carrot, onion and celery in the margarine until crisp tender.
Stir in flour and bacon grease. Pour in chicken broth and milk and stir until smooth.
Add potatoes and stir until mixture is lump free.
Heat until ready to boil, but not boiling.
Serve topped with grated cheddar cheese and chopped green onion.

title: beef pot pie
directions: First cook beef and broth in a covered pan.
(Use broth as part of liquid when cooking potatoes.)
Mix shortening with flour and salt.
Beat egg and add it to dry mixture.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough easy to handle (not sticky).
Roll out dough thin and cut into squares.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.
Garnish with lemon and/or orange slices.
Chill or serve over ice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in large casserole.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Blend in pineapple. Add flour and baking soda.
Mix 3 minutes. Add nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Add the flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa and vanilla (dry mixture).
Gradually add milk. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Grease pan well.

title: barbecue sauce for beef
directions: Heat thoroughly until margarine is completely melted and spices are well blended.
Baste meat continually while grilling or broiling.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an oblong cake pan. Freeze.
Keeps well up to 2 or 3 weeks in the freezer.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies according to package.
While hot, punch holes in top of brownies.
Spoon the 4 tablespoons of liquid over holes. Let cool completely.
Prepare mousse according to package, 1 box at a time.
Crumble 1/2 brownies in a glass bowl or pan.
Spread with layer of mousse (1 box).
Sprinkle Heath Bits.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat another layer, beginning with crumbled brownies and ending with Heath Bits.

title: jello pudding dietetic cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 teaspoon Jell-O dry for topping.
Follow normal method for mixing cake, adding Jell-O and pudding last.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean.
Bake in small 7 or 8-inch cake pan.
Cool completely; put on topping.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cherry cake
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Pour butter over cake mix.
Scatter nuts and coconut over top.
(Do not stir.)
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in small mixer bowl.
Blend in sugar and melted butter.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to butter mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or almost set (pie will not test done).
Cool; cut into wedges.
Serve topped with ice cream, hot fudge sauce and whipped cream.

title: alaskan snow ice cream
directions: Get a large bowl of snow that is white.
In another bowl, mix together canned milk, sugar and flavoring.
Add snow slowly until it reaches the desired consistency.
For stiffer snow ice cream, allow it to freeze in the freezer overnight.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil until brown.
Transfer chicken to baking dish.
Cover chicken with mixture of broth, butter, garlic and seasoning salt to taste.
Top this with the mushrooms.
(The more mushrooms, the better as they will shrink during cooking.) Cook for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: easy layered buckeyes
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Remove from heat. Stir in confectioners sugar, a little at a time, until smooth. Press into an 8-inch pan.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix tomatoes, spaghetti sauce and spices together.
Pour 1/2 of sauce and 1/2 of Parmesan cheese over chicken.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken over, and pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes.
Serve hot with French bread.

title: cheese snack round
directions: Mix the cheese spread and Bisquick.
Shape into roll about 1 inch in diameter on lightly floured wax paper.
Roll in sesame seed, pressing lightly if necessary.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
Cut roll into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on slightly greased (Pam) pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: big daddy's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts together well.
Chill long enough to handle.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry yogurt cake
directions: Cut the angel food cake into 3 layers.
Make a frosting with the Cool Whip, yogurt, food coloring and the strawberries.
Frost between the layers and on the sides.
If using a homemade angel cake, use a 12 ounce Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef, toss and set aside.
Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned. Add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to pan, stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: sugar-free pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Place pecans in bottom of pie shell, then pour mixture over pecans.
Don't stir.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: crock-pot dip
directions: Melt cheese in pot.
Cook sausage and crumble into pieces. Add soup and mix well.
Eat with taco chips.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in flour and cornmeal.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into unbaked shell. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: orange punch
directions: Wash and quarter oranges.
Grind in food chopper.
Dissolve the citric acid in water; add sugar and orange pulp.
Let stand overnight in a crockery jar; strain.
Cover pulp again with water and let stand for several hours.
Strain again.
Mix with the mixture.
Dilute to serve.
Yield:
3 gallons.

title: almond butter cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil; set aside.
Combine almonds and flour in a medium mixing bowl.
Add butter, egg white and vanilla. Stir until combined.
Let mixture stand 10 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Take 1 box of Jell-O and add 1/2 cup water.
Add pineapple. Bring to just a boil.
Let cool.
Add cottage cheese, pecans and condensed milk and pour into a dish and let cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put cracker crumbs with a little melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour or until brown.

title: chocolate ginger zebras
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar and 1/3 cup shortening until light and fluffy.
Add cocoa, corn syrup, milk and egg; blend well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon and cloves; mix well. Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 1 1/2 to 2 hours for easier handling.

title: one rise rolls
directions: Soak yeast in 1/2 cup cold water.
Cream together shortening and sugar; add to this 1/2 cup boiling water and mix until well blended.
Add eggs and then yeast, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients.
When this is mixed, it will be a stiff batter.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
About an hour before serving, roll out. Let rise.
Bake at 400° until as brown as you like.
(Can be shaped into cloverleaf rolls.)
Put in greased muffin tins to brown.

title: taco plate
directions: Brown the meat and onion together in a skillet.
Add the tomato soup and the tomato sauce.
Add barbecue sauce, Tabasco sauce, and worcestershire sauce to your taste.
Simmer 45-60 minutes over low heat.
Serve over taco chips and top with grated cheddar.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a hole, pour in liquid and mix. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour an angel food cake pan.
Pare and slice apples. Mix cinnamon, flour and sugar; sprinkle over apples. Blend remaining ingredients.
Layer batter and apples with last layer being apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: rea beans
directions: Fry bacon; drain all but 1 tablespoon of the grease.
In grease, fry onion until clear.
In separate bowl, mix catsup, sugars, salt, mustard and vinegar.
Drain beans.
Mix everything together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jerome bars
directions: Chill 3 hours or preferably overnight.

title: steak marinade
directions: Sprinkle the following seasonings in order:
salt, pepper, seasoning salt, garlic salt, tenderizer, hickory salt, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Marinate at least 3 hours.

title: fruited turkey kabobs
directions: Prepare grill or heat broiler, if directed by manufacturer. Cut turkey into 1-inch cubes.
In glass bowl combine juice, oil, molasses and herbs and other seasonings; add turkey.
Stir to completely coat turkey; let stand about 15 minutes.
Prepare bell pepper and fruit as directed.
Arrange turkey, bell pepper and fruit alternately on 8 separate skewers.
Grill or broil kabobs about 5-inches from heat source for about 15 to 20 minutes, turning once and basting with marinade left in bowl.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings; contains 216 calories per serving.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix sour cream and soup in a bowl.
Roll beef (sandwich meat) into tight rolls.
Wrap chicken around beef.
Wrap strips of bacon around chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken after placing chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put sugar, vinegar and garlic in blender and blend briefly. With blend on low, slowly add oil.
When oil is incorporated, add poppy seeds and refrigerate.
Yields 3 1/2 cups and is good on meats, fruits, raw veggies, and boiled eggs.

title: pasta with tomato, basil & brie
directions: Combine garlic (I use more), tomatoes, brie (works fine not in cubes too), basil (use a bit less), olive oil, salt and pepper in the pasta serving dish. Set aside. DO NOT MIX. It needs to be at room temperature so it's okay to do way ahead. Cover. Cook pasta until al dente. Drain and immediately add to bowl. Toss well. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve at once. Excellent!

title: hunter's chicken
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan.
Salt, pepper and paprika chicken to taste.
Flour chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, in margarine. Bake for 30 minutes in a 400° oven.
Put soup and water in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Turn chicken.
Pour soup over chicken.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring to boil first 4 ingredients; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper with teaspoon.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken parts
in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients;
pour over chicken.
Bake
oven about 1 hour or until done, basting frequently.

title: strawberry fudge revel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 12-c. Bundt cake pan or tube pan, 10x4 inches.
Mix brown sugar, flour, cocoa and margarine until crumbly; reserve.
Beat cake mix (dry), water, oil and eggs in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl frequently, 2 minutes.
Pour about 1 2/3 c. batter into pan; sprinkle with about 1 1/3 c. of the crumbly mixture.
Pour about 1 2/3 c. batter into pan; sprinkle with remaining crumbly mixture.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; invert on wire rack or heatproof serving plate.
Remove pan; cool cake completely. Spread top of cake with Chocolate Glaze, allowing some to drizzle down side.

title: pecan pies
directions: Lightly beat eggs by hand; add sugar.
Add all remaining ingredients, saving pecans for last.
Stir well; pour into two 9-inch pie crusts or one deep-dish pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; lower heat to 350° and finish baking (two pies:
about 40 additional minutes; one deep-dish pie:
about 50 additional minutes).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: After rice and broccoli are cooked, strain off any water.
Add butter, chopped onion and celery, then add your Campbell's golden mushroom soup.
Pour in your jar of Cheez Whiz (after melting it in microwave).
Stir all together, then place in your casserole dish and bake at 350°.
M-M-M-Good!!!

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cookies and oleo.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve some crumbs for the top.
Mix together milk and pudding in a bowl.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Combine both mixtures and stir well.
Pour over cookies and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: ham and fruit strata
directions: In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, layer bread, ham, chopped pears and shredded cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and nutmeg and pour evenly into dish.
Cover and chill 4 to 24 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until center is set and golden top.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with additional pears.
Makes 4 servings.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and vinegar.
Add flour until rolls out easily on a floured surface.
Roll thin; cut in strips.
Dry on racks.
Boil in chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sally's refrigerator veggies
directions: Layer cucumbers, onions, squash and bell peppers to fill wide-mouth gallon jar.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Stir syrup until dissolved, then pour over veggies layered in jar. Refrigerate 2 weeks, then ready to eat.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in heavy 2 quart saucepan.
Add sugar, syrup and water.
Stir often and cook to hard crack stage (300°).
Quickly stir in chopped nuts and spread in well greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan.
Cool and turn out on wax paper.
Spread with half the chocolate and sprinkle with half the finely chopped almonds. Cover with wax paper, invert and repeat chocolate and nuts.
Chill to firm and break.
Be sure to watch carefully after 260 degrees. You may use toasted pecans instead of almonds.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in casserole dish uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheddary corn pudding
directions: In a bowl thoroughly mix corn, egg, milk, cheese, flour, sugar and 1 tablespoon butter.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Toss crumbs with remaining 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle over.
Bake in 350° oven until pudding is firm, about 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
After frozen, can be placed in plastic storage bag in freezer until needed.
Bake frozen balls in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: sweet pepper pickles(easy to make)
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar together to make hot syrup.
Wash peppers and dry.
Remove seeds and cut in thin strips with scissors.
Scald in hot water a few seconds.
Drain and drop into ice water to crisp.
Drain.
Put in hot, sterilized jars and fill with hot syrup.
Seal immediately.

title: old fashioned cooked salad dressing
directions: For leaf lettuce or other greens:
In saucepan mix sugar and salt.
Stir in vinegar and water and bring to a boil.
Stir small amount into beaten egg, then stir egg into saucepan and let boil. Remove from heat and stir in oleo.
Cool.

title: curried walnut dip
directions: Puree cottage cheese, marmalade, onion, curry powder, salt and liquid red pepper in blender; add walnuts and whirl to finely chop.
Add sour cream; whirl to blend.
Scrape into serving bowl. Chill several hours for flavors to mellow.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Bake at 350°.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and margarine. Blend at low speed until crumbly; stir in nuts.
Press 2 3/4 cups of crumbs into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: yankee chili
directions: In skillet brown chuck with onion, cloves and pepper.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in a casserole dish.

title: hot slaw
directions: Mix everything together and top with Italian dressing. Set overnight.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions and drain. Separate or they will stick together.
Cool.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Put your favorite spaghetti sauce on the bottom of a pan.
Squeeze the shells lightly and they will open for easy filling.
Fill each with a generous portion of the cheese mixture.
Put shells on top of sauce and pour more sauce on top. Sprinkle with more oregano and shredded cheese.
Bake in warm oven to heat and serve.

title: blue kraut deluxe
directions: Wash and drain prepared cabbage and cut in quarters.
Discard core and tough ribs and shred cabbage.
Fry bacon in a large skillet until browned.
Add sugar to hot fat and saute slowly until golden.
Add apple and onion.
Cover and braise over very low heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Place shredded cabbage in skillet or Dutch oven with cover.
Slowly pour vinegar and jelly over kraut and stir to mix well.
Cover and braise slowly for 10 minutes.
Add water, cover and let simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until cabbage is fork-tender.
Yields 6.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
When frozen, mix and spoon into a tall glass.
Add Sprite or 7-Up.

title: fruit medley
directions: Use juice from pineapple to mix pudding.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: granola bars
directions: Lightly grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spoon mixture into prepared pan.
With oiled fingers, press out firmly and evenly into pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Cool at least 2 hours before cutting or they will fall apart.
Makes 32 bars at 195 calories each.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix everything in a 13 x 10 x 2-inch pan; do not grease.
Mix the flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda.
Stir all this together with a fork.
Then make 3 indented holes in this mixture.
In one, put the vanilla.
In the second, put the oil.
In the last one, put the vinegar.
Pour 2 cups of cold water over all and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; let cool.
Run knife down sides and loosen bottom with spatula.

title: fruit and cereal brunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix cereal and orange juice in a large bowl.
Let stand until soft. Mix in oil, egg and bananas.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pans and bake for 45 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake covered 15 to 20 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch and oregano in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Pour heated tomatoes over chicken.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix all together (except yeast) and add 5 cups whole wheat flour.
Then add yeast.
Let rise for 20 minutes, then add 4 cups white flour.
If more is needed add from cup number 5.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 big loaves or 5 small ones.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, and salt together into a bowl. Set aside.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, undrained fruit cocktail, 1 cup of the coconut and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Bring margarine, sugar and milk to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Stir in remaining 1 1/3 cup coconut; spoon over warm cake.
Top with prepared whipped topping if desired.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Allow to thicken slightly. Add fruits and chill.

title: mushroom strudels *
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter; add mushrooms, shallots, salt and pepper to taste, wine and tarragon.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until most of liquid has evaporated and mixture is mushy. Let cool slightly.
Stir in sour cream.
Spread 1 sheet phyllo on a damp cloth.
Keep other sheets covered with another damp cloth.
Brush the opened sheet generously with melted butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Using a spoon, form about half the mushroom mixture into a sausage shape along the bottom of the phyllo sheet.
Fold over the bottom edge of the phyllo to enclose the filling.
Lift the towel gently so that the phyllo envelops the filling and roll like a jelly roll.
Brush top generously with melted butter.
Continue filling other sheets in the same way until all filling is used up.
Place the strudels on a buttered baking sheet.
Using a sharp knife, cut the strudels into individual servings, about 1 1/2 inches wide.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until crisp and well browned.
Makes 15 to 20.

title: crusty whole wheat bread
directions: Heat the milk, water and margarine to 120°.
In large mixing bowl, combine 1 cup whole wheat flour, 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour, yeast and salt.
Add milk mixture and beat well with mixer. Stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead for 5 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over melted margarine.
Pour fruit with juice over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: one-pan magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan). Use 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt butter. Pour milk over crumbs. Top with other ingredients. Press down gently. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until browned. Cool before cutting. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: chicken divan squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles. Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; distribute broccoli and chicken evenly over crust.

title: pork and scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onion.
Dot bottom of casserole dish with the butter.
Layer potatoes, onion, salt and pepper. Repeat.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover with undiluted mushroom soup.
Put cover on casserole.
Bake at 325° for about an hour or until done.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Blend until crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups for topping.
Press remaining mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add eggs, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread mixture of baked crust; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix as they are listed. Pour on hot grill.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; let cool.
Mix yeast, sugar and water together.
Set for 10 minutes and then add to the first 6 ingredients.
Add flour a little at a time.
Turn out and knead. Let rise to double in size, punch down and rise again.
Put into pans and rise.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook meat and onions until meat is brown.
Add salt.
Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray and fry tortillas until limp. Spoon equal amounts of meat mixture on tortillas.
Top each with taco sauce and cheese.
Roll up; place seam side down in lightly greased 6 x 10-inch pan.

title: rice mushroom casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish or oblong pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef in food processor.
Save enough to put on top of cheese ball when it is mixed and formed.
Return to refrigerator and chill.
It is much easier to make if cheese is soft; ball is easier to handle.

title: bacon tomato spaghetti
directions: Chop up the bacon and onion.
Fry with 1/2 teaspoon garlic together in skillet.
Drain all the grease.
Stir in the tomatoes and add chili powder to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: smash cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, oil, margarine and nuts.
Put in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: baked apples and sauce
directions: Bake apples (partially peeled and cored) until softened, 1/2 hour.
You may fill centers with raisins, if desired.
Boil both sugars, flour, salt, molasses, water, butter and vanilla until slightly thickened.
Serve over apples.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: You will need a medium mixing bowl.

title: pineapple orange sauce
directions: Combine pineapple, 1/2 cup orange juice and 1 teaspoon orange peel with remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Cool. Serve over ice cream, frozen yogurt, pancakes or waffles.
Makes 8 servings

title: cheese filled coffee cake
directions: Mix yeast, milk and sugar and let stand until dissolved.
Mix flour and salt and cut into cold margarine.
Add egg yolks and yeast mixture; mix well.

title: mock whip cream icing
directions: Cook flour and milk together on stove to thicken; cool.
Add rest of ingredients to mixer bowl.
Beat 7 or more minutes.

title: cucumber-lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add lemon juice and onion juice.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in cucumber and mayonnaise. Pour into one large mold or individual molds.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Blend
in
sweet
potatoes.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add alternately with milk. Do not overmix.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3
full.
Bake
25 minutes in preheated 400° oven. Yield: 3 dozen muffins.

title: butter tarts
directions: Beat well the egg, brown sugar and butter.
Add 1 cup raisins and 1/4 cup water.
The more water, the juicier...less water, more firm.
Bake in unbaked pastry shells.
My grandmother's recipe handed down to my mother.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flour 9 x 13-inch dish.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost while cake is still warm.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Grease casserole and put tortilla chips (crushed) in bottom of large casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put shredded chicken, soup, milk, green chiles and onion in a saucepan and heat until hot and bubbly.
Pour over chips and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook the chicken, onion and peppers in desired quantities. Brown in wok in small amount of oil until done.
Stir in desired amount of teriyaki sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: red bean chili
directions: Brown meat and drain well. Add your seasoning and fry down until onions are clear. Now boil your beans. When they start to crack open, add your tomato sauce, meat mixture and Ro-Tel tomatoes to beans. Finish cooking them by adding your chili seasoning to the pot. Cook on low to medium heat until thick and creamy. Remember to smash your beans on the side of the pot when you stir for cream ones.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Place in 1-quart casserole dish. Layer next 2 ingredients over ground beef. Top with soup and milk mixed together. Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Place cheese on top. Put back in oven, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine, potatoes, sour cream, undiluted chicken soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Put into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans or 1 greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
(Don't make casserole too thick.)
Cover with topping made with crushed corn flakes and other stick of margarine.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Simmer 8 to 10 hours in crock-pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with icing. Double for large cake.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: In large pan, brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Rinse cooked hamburger in colander to rinse off excess fat.
Cut tortillas in triangles and layer 1/2 in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 hamburger, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 triangle tortillas, 1/2 hamburger, 1/2 cottage cheese and cheese.
Then pour both cans of enchilada sauce over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Excellent.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt marshmallows.
Add a little milk and stir constantly. Break up chocolate bar and add rest of milk.
Stir until smooth and let cool.

title: egg and cheese pie
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll rolls and separate into triangles.
Arrange in 9-inch pie plate to make crust, pressing edges together; flute edge.
Sprinkle bacon over bottom.
Top with tomato slices, then cheese.

title: golden peach pie
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1/2 c. of the syrup (you should have about 2-2/3 c. peaches).
Combine sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt. Add reserved syrup.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Slice in squares.
Top with Cool Whip.
Yield: 9 servings.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
In a large bowl, mix salad oil, lemon juice, chili powder and salt.
Gently stir in green beans, green chilies and diced avocado.
Arrange Boston lettuce leaves on 4 dinner plates.
Top with bean salad.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put fruit filling on bottom, then pineapple.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix.
Do not mix.
Slice oleo over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dessert
directions: Slice angel food cake and place in 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan. Layer ingredients on cake in order given.
Top with strawberries (optional).

title: raspberry-almond dream
directions: Place raspberries in blender or food processor.
Whirl until pureed.
Place whipped topping in large bowl.
Gradually fold in raspberry puree, confectioners sugar and almond extract.
Spoon into dessert dishes and refrigerate or freeze until ready to serve.
Garnish with dollop of whipped topping, if you wish.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Put vegetables in and stir carefully while boiling for about 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed at 350° in a round 8-inch pan and a round 9-inch pan.
Place the 8-inch layer in the bottom of the punch bowl.
Take one-half of each of the ingredients and spread on cake (one at a time).
Place the 9-inch layer on top of this.
Do the same as with the first layer.
Garnish with coconut and pecans and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 35 people.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Put washed shrimp in a large roasting pan.
Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add pepper, salad dressing, lemon juice and rest of ingredients.
Pour over raw shrimp.
Marinate overnight.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Test after 30 minutes.
Serve on a platter.
Sauce is delicious for dunking.

title: daddy's black twig cookies
directions: Cream the shortening. Add sugar gradually; blend well. Add egg and vanilla. Blend. Sift dry ingredients and add to shortening mixture alternately with apple butter. Blend well. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Keep 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until edges brown. Remove with spatula and cool on wire rack.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Put into ovenproof dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 1 cup.

title: nana's zucchini bread
directions: Beat oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; set aside.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini; fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 greased bread pans or greased tube pan.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook sausage and beef until brown.
Mix baking mix and water until dough forms. Divide in half.
Place larger portion in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese.
Cover with 3/4 of sauce.
Add meat and other toppings.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Place remaining dough on top.
Seal to bottom dough.
Make small slits in top crust.
Spread with remaining pizza sauce and cheese.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes.

title: tea cakes #2
directions: Cream sugar and
butter.
Add
eggs
and mix well.
Add flour and mix
well,
making
a
stiff
dough.
Knead
well on floured cloth or wax paper and roll to desired thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 325° until lightly browned.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves, salt, sour cream and eggs; stir well and fold in raisins.
Spoon mixture into pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked fruit
directions: Drain peaches, pears and pineapple in a colander.
Drain apricots and keep separate from other fruit.
Put all fruit except apricots in a large bowl.
Add raisins, walnuts, 1/2 cup brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix lightly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and place apricots evenly on top.
Cut toasted bread slices into 1/2-inch squares and place on top.
Pour melted butter and balance of brown sugar over entire mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break up bread in a bowl.
Heat milk, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Beat eggs well and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package. Drain and put in rectangular pan.
Cut stick of butter up and put on noodles.
Mix.
Empty drained can of peas on top of noodles.

title: midnight cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Mix cocoa with water, then add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Grease two bread pans.
Mix together by hand (spoon) the cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream, oil and water.
Pour mixture into pans.
Before baking, add topping.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and nuts; put on top of bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill until very thick, then fold in carrots and pecans.
Pour into individual molds or a 1-quart mold or double recipe and pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.

title: jelly with fruit cocktail
directions: Use 1 cup each fruit cocktail juice, grape juice and apple juice and add lemon juice, sugar and fruit jell pectin.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly, for 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour into jars; wipe tops to make sure they're clean.
Put on tops and bands to seal.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat V-8 juice.
Dissolve gelatine (one at a time).
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and jar of chili sauce.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: honey baked chicken breasts
directions: In a large baking dish (9 x 13-inch), melt butter. Stir in honey, pineapple juice, mustard, salt and curry powder. Coat chicken well and arrange in baking dish. Bake about 1 hour at 375° (uncovered).
Turn at least once during baking. Serves 4.

title: rice & sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole.
Bake with top on at 325 F for 1 1/2 hrs.

title: one, two, three, four cake
directions: Mix together and bake in tube pan at 350° until cake tester comes out clean.

title: chicken charlie casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package instructions, then spread out in the bottom of a large baking pan.
Boil chicken until done; cool.
Remove meat from bone; layer evenly over rice.
Season to taste.
Prepare vegetables according to packaging and layer over chicken.
Mix together and heat soups; pour over vegetables. Crush crackers and completely cover casserole.
Melt butter in microwave and pour over crust.
Bake at about 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Mix all pudding ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased, round cake pans.
Top with Vanilla Sauce Topping.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: In 9-inch unbaked pie crust, place these ingredients: Combine eggs and milk; add sugar, flour and nutmeg, then rhubarb.
Dot ingredients in shell with butter.
Add top crust.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.
(May cover lightly with foil.)

title: brownies
directions: In medium pan, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: scallops with vermicelli
directions: Rinse scallops.
Combine scallops, lemon juice and parsley in glass dish.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator while preparing sauce.
Cook and stir onion and garlic in oil and 1 tablespoon of the butter in large skillet over medium-high heat until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes with juice, basil, oregano and thyme. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes stirring occasionally.
Drain scallops. Cook and stir scallops in remaining 1 tablespoon butter in another large skillet over medium heat until scallops are opaque about 2 minutes.
Add cream and tomato sauce.
Pour sauce over vermicelli in large bowl.
Toss gently to coat.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese and flour in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place 1/2-inch apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 20 servings.

title: bierocks
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion.
Drain well.
Add salt and pepper, mix together with sauerkraut.
Place tablespoonful of filling in center of 5 inch square of bread dough.
Close and pinch together corners and set onto greased baking sheet to rise. Bake at 350 degrees till golden brown, 20-25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Cook yellow
rice
as
directed
on package.
Mix rice, Mexicorn, soup
and margarine together.
Melt margarine before mixing with other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well and add a few drops of lemon juice.
Place in a shallow dish and cover with Chathoms Seafood sauce.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine the first eleven ingredients.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in lightly buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: passover rolls
directions: Combine matzo meal, salt and pepper. Bring oil and water to a boil.
Add to matzo mixture.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
With oiled hands, shape into rolls and place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni, cucumber, onion, tomato, relish and eggs.
Add salad dressing and seasonings.
May need more salad dressing in order to make salad moist.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put rice, margarine and salt into mixing bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Crumble corn flakes over the top.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbles go all the way through.

title: clam chowder from rhode island
directions: Render pork and add onions.
Cook until clear. Add potatoes and clams.
Cover with water and cook until potatoes are done. Add some milk if you must!

title: country style spareribs
directions: Bake spareribs 1 hour at 425° to 450°, then pour off fat.
Mix remaining ingredients together and boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour the sauce over ribs and baste occasionally for 2 to 3 hours or longer at 250°.

title: lemon coolers
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Before using, mix again.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons in a glass and add 7-Up.
Mix.
Can add booze if desired.
Will keep a week or more in refrigerator.
Use when desired.
A good summer drink, refreshing!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown
beef in 10-inch skillet;
drain.
Chop mushrooms, pepper and onions and saute in margarine until tender.
Mix all ingredients
in large saucepan; bring to boil, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: delicious chewy macaroons
directions: Blend together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until light golden brown.
Let cool and eat!

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn in 1 1/2 pints vinegar for 30 minutes.
Then put all together and add 1 pint more vinegar, then cook 20 minutes longer. Then seal while hot.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed and let cool.
Drain juice from artichokes,
then mix all ingredients together and serve. (You may add
a
dash
of
curry
powder
to mayonnaise if you desire.)

title: blueberry delight
directions: Blend graham crackers, sugar and melted butter and press in an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and cream cheese together until creamy and spread over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Spread one can of pie filling over cooled dessert.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip.

title: potatoes in a white sauce
directions: Place diced potatoes in saucepan.
Just cover with water. Bring to a boil, then simmer over medium heat for 20 minutes. Combine margarine, flour and salt.
Add to milk in a separate saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring until smooth.
Mix together sauce and potatoes until well blended. Place in serving dish.

title: no-cook icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Add cut up marshmallows and heat until melted.
Pour over crackers and fruit.
Mix well.
Add pecans.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend after each one.
Sift all dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Cook in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Let ingredients come to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Cool until thick enough to spread.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until light.
Add well beaten egg and applesauce.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices together and add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased cake pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.

title: peanut brittle(700 watt microwave)
directions: With this formula in mind, a casserole may be made of any ingredients you have on hand which you think might be a good combination.
Use the following as a guide:

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
In 1-quart saucepan, over medium heat, cook frozen onion until tender.
Stir in soup and cream cheese cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and hot.

title: my papaw's blueberry pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar until soft.
Pour into crust. Layer blueberries, then pecans and repeat.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Cut steak in serving pieces.
Brown on both sides.
Drain off grease.
Add onion, sliced in thin slices.
Add mushroom soup plus 1 1/2 cans of water and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add fresh tomato when almost done.

title: country garden sandwiches
directions: Mix cucumber, tomato, green pepper, onion, sugar, wine vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or longer.
When ready to prepare sandwiches, drain mixture in sieve for at least 1 hour.
Let cream cheese reach room temperature and soften with enough milk to spread easily.
Trim crusts from bread; spread with cream cheese, then vegetable mix. Makes 8 to 10 sandwiches.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in heavy kettle; drain.
Add all ingredients except green beans.
Bring to boil; lower heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add green beans; bring to boil and simmer until beans are tender.
Add more water if you prefer a thinner soup. Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: fried apples
directions: Slice apples into skillet with melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook gently, stirring occasionally for about 4 minutes or until apples are tender.
Uncover and continue cooking, stirring a bit, until syrup thickens.
Serve as a meat accompaniment or as a dessert.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Add fruit and 1 cup of sugar; dissolve by heating.
Add vanilla, if desired.
Melt margarine in pan.
Pour dough mixture in (flour, sugar, baking powder and milk).
Add fruit.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Heat cider with powdered spices and sugar for about 10 minutes over low heat, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Serve hot in punch cups.
Makes 25 cups.

title: cubed beef and rice
directions: Brown stew meat in oil.
Add tomato juice.
Pressure cook 45 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Add mushroom soup (undiluted). Serve over rice.

title: zucchini corn casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water until just tender, about 6 minutes.
Drain zucchini, cut in chunks and combine with the corn and eggs.

title: vaughan's potatoes
directions: In saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling unsalted water about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain and mash. Stir in Parmesan cheese, cream cheese, butter or margarine, green onion, onion soup mix, pepper and hot pepper sauce. Mix well. Add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk if mixture is dry. Shape mixture into 8 balls.
Dip in beaten egg. Roll in cornflakes. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot and crisp. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Pour water over broccoli.
Heat until broccoli has thawed. Stir in rice, celery, onion, butter and soup.
Stir over low heat until butter has melted and ingredients are thoroughly blended. Stir in cheese spread. Cover and bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk and flavoring.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.
Add fruit or flavoring at this time (before freezing).

title: taffy
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar, corn syrup, water and butter in saucepan and mix well.
Cook to a hard ball stage, stirring frequently (hard ball stage about 265°).
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.
When cool, pull until it gets satiny and porous.
Twist into a rope; cut into 1/2 or 1-inch pieces.

title: ratatouille nicoise(cuisine a la josette; yield:  12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add the onions and saute until they begin to color.
Remove to a large, deep baking dish.
Add a little more oil.
Repeat the operation with the zucchini, the eggplant and the green pepper (be careful not to scorch the latter).
Add all the remaining ingredients and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage 10 minutes.
Put in baking dish and cover with sauce of melted butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese to sauce and pour over cabbage.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top and brown 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix half of dressing with margarine.
Line casserole dish with mixture.
Combine rest of ingredients and add the rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly and a little brown.
Freezes well.

title: veg nut patties
directions: Mix together and fry in small patties.
Pour over them 1 can mushroom soup that has been mixed with 3/4 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hurry up and wait cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread pie filling evenly in bottom of pan.
Next layer a can of drained pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over fruit layers.
Melt 2 sticks of butter or margarine and pour over mixture.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, unsalted.

Combine eggs, cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Arrange broccoli spears in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Spoon cheese mixture atop. Stir together bread crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato broccoli bake
directions: Steam potatoes in steamer for 5 minutes.
Blanch broccoli in steamer for 5 minutes.
Heat milk in suitably sized kettle.
Make a roux by blending margarine and flour; mix together well.
Slowly add roux to hot milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add steamed potatoes, broccoli, salt, paprika, onions, cottage cheese, mayo and dill weed.
Mix together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Calories 149/serving, 65 gm fat/serving, 6 mg cholesterol/serving and 374 mg sodium/serving.

title: tuna noodle supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, stir together sour cream, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, milk and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add hot pasta, tuna, broccoli, red pepper and green onion. Stir until evenly blended.
Place tuna mixture in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover, bake 40 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 (1 1/3-cup) servings.

title: mulled cider
directions: Heat 15 minutes over medium heat until warm.

title: mexi-cano casserole
directions: Line a large casserole dish with flour tortillas.
Next, layer meat, beans and onion.
(Do not drain beans.)
Next, add cheese. Cover with layer of tortillas.
Spread cream of celery soup over tortillas and pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over soup layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Do not overbeat!
Spoon batter into twelve 2 1/2-inch greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly touched.
Serve warm.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, milk, melted butter and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until done.
(Insert table knife; when it comes out clean, pie is done.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grate carrots. Mix oil and sugar, add 1 egg at a time beating well. Add dry ingredients. Stir in carrots and pecans. Bake in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan or bundt pan for 40 minutes.

title: reese cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Form into flat round balls. Melt together paraffin and chocolate chips.
Let cool.
Dip the balls into chocolate chip mixture.
Put on wax paper.
You may use a toothpick or a fork to dip the balls.

title: salmon log
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Roll into log and chill several hours.
Combine pecans and parsley.
Roll chilled log in nut mixture to coat.
Serve with crackers.

title: ron's never-fail microwave fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients (except peanut butter) together.
Put in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Beat with electric mixer. Add 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Pour into small pan or fudge dish.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add prunes and fold in nuts.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: honeyed carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; cook over low heat for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Keep broth.
Drain canned vegetables and mix with cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup, add 1 1/2 cans of chicken broth.
Mix together in bowl.
Chop chicken and line casserole dish.
Pour vegetables over chicken. Mix flour, buttermilk and margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cajun baked rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in two covered dishes at 325° for 1 hour.

title: turtles
directions: Mix caramels and milk.
Add nuts and drop on waxed paper. Cool 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax.
Dip caramel and nut combination in chocolate.
Put on waxed paper to set.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Serves 2 to 3.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: rosemary au gratin potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add the cream.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the rosemary, garlic, salt, pepper and potatoes. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: First Layer:
On a large platter, spread cans of jalapeno bean dip, mashed avocados mixed together with lemon juice and salt and pepper.

title: garden pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a
9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Press seams together.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill and minced onion.
Cut vegetables in small pieces.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled crescent rolls, then spread vegetables on top.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape mixture into 3 dozen tiny meatballs.
Place in pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
It is not necessary to turn meatballs as they bake. Insert toothpick into each one.
Serve with hot barbecue sauce.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine everything but peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Cook over medium heat until forms a ball in cold water.
Then add peanut butter, vanilla and walnuts or pecans.
Beat until it is not glossy.
Take a short time to cook and heat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Form into small balls.

title: breakfast squares
directions: The night before, cut bread slices into small cubes.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Add bread cubes and allow to soak.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Lightly grease 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Layer sausage and cheese in dish.
Pour egg mixture on top and mix gently.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chili pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Stir in salt, pepper and chili powder.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, egg and milk.
Pour or place over hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Carefully turn out on large platter. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Make up Jiffy cake mix according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 15-inch pan.
Make up pudding mix, using just 1 cup of milk.
Add cream cheese and spread over cooled cake.
Drain pineapple and spread over pudding mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and nuts, if desired.

title: corn pie
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish. Place pats of butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: seafood salad
