directions: Cook shrimp and macaroni.
In a large bowl after shrimp and macaroni cool, mix all other ingredients and refrigerate for one hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix hamburger, sausage, cracker crumbs, onions, salt, pepper and bell pepper with tomato sauce.
If too soft, add a small amount of crumbs.
If too stiff, add ketchup until right consistency.
Mold into shape to fit desired cooking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 40 minutes; drain off excess grease and cook 20 more minutes.
Drain and pour ketchup over loaf and cook 15 more minutes.

title: red bean toss
directions: In bowl, combine kidney beans, chili beans, celery, pickles, onions and cheese.
In another bowl, combine salt, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Toss with bean mixture.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with corn chips.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: hall's chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and cocoa in one bowl.
Beat eggs in a small bowl.
Add salad oil to these ingredients.
Add buttermilk and vanilla to eggs and mix into the dry ingredients.
Add baking soda in hot water last.
Mix in.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Use toothpick to test for doneness.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine margarine and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in vanilla; mix well.
Stir in powdered sugar and beat frosting until creamy.
Add only enough milk to make frosting of spreading consistency.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and water in double boiler, then add all the pecans you can.
Stir and drop on wax paper and chill.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix
together cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla. Bake sugar
cookie
dough
at
and let cool.
Pour cream cheese mixture
over
sugar cookie pizza crust, then drop the fruit on the crust and let cool.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; toss to coat.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Pour dressing over carrots in large nonstick skillet; stir to coat.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in almonds and parsley. Makes 6 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: cream of beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Cook noodles.
Mix hamburger, noodles and cream cheese.
Top with cheese and bake 20 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Make mixture of chicken, tomatoes, soups, broth and onion. Then layer in a casserole dish tortilla chips, chicken mixture, cheese and repeat.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel pudding
directions: Stir together the sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in a saucepan. Add boiling water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When thick, remove from stove and add vanilla and butter.
This recipe can also be used for pies.
Just pour into a cooked pie shell. Makes enough for 1 pie.

title: lasagne spinach spirals
directions: Drain spinach well, squeezing out excess juice.
Prepare lasagne according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
Place vegetable oil in a medium-sized nonstick skillet and heat over medium-high heat.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Mix in spinach.
Set aside and cool slightly.
In a large mixing bowl, combine spinach mixture, Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses, egg and spices.
Spread spinach mixture equally on lasagne and roll up each piece jelly-roll style.
Place half of the spaghetti sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place pasta spinach spirals, seam-side down, in dish.
Top with remaining spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until heated, about 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dust lightly with flour.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into a large bowl.
Make a well in center and add
in order the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in carrots, coconut, walnut and pineapple until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Can also be baked in a tube pan for 55 to 60 minutes.
Spread with cream cheese frosting or powdered sugar.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: In bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken in baking pan and pour over the lemon and oil mixture. Cover and bake until tender.
Baste occasionally.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer to allow chicken to brown.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes until tender.
Drain.
In large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, butter, garlic powder and pepper.
With mixer, beat until fluffy.
Pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Cook chocolate on High for 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in cream cheese until smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar, nuts, coconut, grated chocolate, cookie crumbs or sprinkles.
Store in the refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: sugar-free muffins
directions: Sift flour, sweetener, baking powder, salt and soda and mix with oats.
Melt butter in pan.
Add milk, egg, mashed bananas or applesauce, vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Pour wet mixture into dry mixture and stir lightly.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: crunchy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and mash.
Add sour cream, butter and egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Add onion, seasoning and a little milk (if it needs thinning).
Place in buttered casserole.
Combine cornflakes, cheese and melted butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: celery and pecan casserole
directions: Cook celery in water with sugar until tender; drain.
Mix with pecans.
Make cream sauce by melted butter, blend in flour and stir in cream until thick.
Add salt, pepper and beaten egg.
Add celery and nuts.
Pour in buttered dish and top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake until brown on top, about 30 minutes, at 325° to 350°.
Good!

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika or bacon bits, if desired. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Mix together and pour into greased pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or 325° in glass baking dish.
Partly cool in pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skin until tender.
Peel and slice into large bowl while still hot.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water. Add sugar, vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and pour over the potatoes while they are still hot.
Let stand for several hours.
Add diced pickles and onion; mix well.
Add oil.
Serve cold.
Serves 4.

title: winter chowder
directions: Partially cook bacon; stir in onion.
Cook until bacon is crisp.
Stir in water, potatoes, carrots and chicken bouillon. Heat to boiling until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Add milk, corn and pepper.
Mix cheese and flour, stirring constantly until melted.

title: potato soup
directions: Place vegetables in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cover with broth and water to 1-inch over vegetables.
Simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Do not drain.

title: zesty fiesta corn
directions: In large bowl, stir together seasoning mix and water until blended.
Add oil and vinegar.
Add corn and other ingredients. Toss lightly.
Chill several hours; stir and serve.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove skin and fat from meat and cut in cubes.
Use mostly white meat.
Mix with dressing and celery and arrange on lettuce in salad bowl.
Garnish with green peppers.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix crumbs and baking powder.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla. Stir in coconut, pineapple and nuts.
Serve topped with whipped cream.
My family likes it with ice cream.

title: apple sheet cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat together eggs and sugar until well blended.
Add oil; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly; do not overbeat. Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a well-greased 11 x 15-inch sheet cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: philly bars
directions: Mix 1 egg, stick of butter, and cake mix.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat remaining 3 eggs.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: In Dutch oven, bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Add cereal and mix well.
Turn out into buttered cake pan.
Cool and ice with chocolate icing.

title: green bean lyonnaise
directions: Cook beans as directed.
Melt butter and saute onions in saucepan.
Add cooked beans with remaining ingredients.
Simmer until tender.

title: fruit and wine medley
directions: Combine orange juice, wine, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix and let set.
Place cut up fruits in bowl.
Pour juice mixture over fruit and toss lightly.
Cover and chill slightly before serving.

title: supper casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: betty lu's bran muffins
directions: Mix all-bran and boiling water and let it set while you do the following:

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat together sugar, butter, flour, lemon rind and juice and egg yolks until light in color and texture.
Add milk and stir well.
Beat egg whites until fluffy (not dry) and fold in.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake until top turns golden. Makes 1 pie.
Bake at 350°.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Add chicken, celery, onion and seasoning to stock.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cover and cook until noodles are almost tender (5 to 10 minutes).

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Serve over ice and garnish with cherries.
Yields about 3 quarts.

title: praline brownies
directions: Mix batter for cake brownies, but do not add nuts.
Spread batter in greased baking pan.
Melt butter; stir in brown sugar and pecans.
Sprinkle evenly over the batter.
Bake at 350° about 28 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Combine in a large bowl the 1 cup flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and butter to form the "crumbs."
Press half of the crumbs into the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: no frying fish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix milk and hot sauce together and stir well. Soak fish filets about 20 minutes or so; drain well and roll in breadcrumbs. Line pan with foil and place fish in single layer in pan. Spray butter on top of breadcrumbs and then drizzle lemon juice (not much, just drop by drop). Bake until golden brown or bake for 30 minutes, then put in broiler to brown.

title: chewy homemade breadsticks
directions: In a large mixer bowl, sprinkle yeast over the water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in salad oil, sugar, salt, milk and 2 cups flour.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes or until dough pulls from sides of bowl in stretchy strands.
Stir in more flour (about 1 cup) to form a stiff dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead for 10 minutes or until smooth.
Turn dough over in a lightly greased bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise in a dark place for 1 hour or until doubled.
Turn dough out onto a board. Knead to expel trapped air.
Cut into 12 equal pieces.
Cover and let rest for 5 minutes.
Roll each piece out into a log, about 12-inches long.
Set breadsticks, 1-inch apart, on a greased baking sheet.
Brush tops lightly with oil.
Sprinkle with caraway seed. Let rise in a warm place for 20 minutes or until puffy.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on pan for 2 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease miniature muffin tins generously.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in chile.
Whisk together egg, melted butter and buttermilk; stir into dry ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Fill prepared tins about 3/4 full. Bake 10 minutes or until light brown.
Serve warm.

title: garlic bread
directions: Spread on French bread that has been cut lengthwise.
Sprinkle with paprika and broil.

title: greek cheese pie (tyropita)
directions: Beat eggs until light and creamy.
Fold into combined cheeses. Season to taste.
Place 8 pastry sheets in buttered casserole dish.
Butter each sheet with melted butter.
Pour cheese mixture over filo dough and cover with 8 more buttered pastry sheets. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm. Serves 6.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter or oleo until tender.
Do not brown.
Add pared and cubed potatoes, celery, parsley, salt, pepper and water to cover vegetables by about 1 inch.
Cook until tender. Mash about half of potato mix, then add the milk and reheat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Great served with buttered toast.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Beat butter in a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer until softened.
Add the 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon; beat until combined.
Beat with water and vanilla.
Stir in flour and toasted pecans with wooden spoon.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients like making dressing.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.
(Preheat oven.)

title: dirty potatoes
directions: Scrub and wash potatoes; do not peel them. Cube potatoes. Butter a 2-quart Corning Ware dish. Put a layer of potatoes; sprinkle with garlic salt, celery seed and Parmesan cheese, then cut up little pieces of butter and put on top. Put another layer of potatoes and sprinkle the ingredients. Continue to do this until dish is full. Top with pieces of butter. Put lid on dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Use as much ingredients to suit your taste.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 5-quart hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: 7-up chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breast fillets in the first 3 ingredients for 4 to 6 hours or overnight and grill.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Bake pastry shell at 400° for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg; beat until blended. Gradually stir in milk and mix well.
Pour filling into pastry shell; sprinkle with additional nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Store in refrigerator.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites until they will hold a stiff peak.
Gradually add sugar (beat on low).
Add cream of tartar, vanilla and almond extract.
Gradually fold in very carefully and slowly the flour mixture.

title: crock-pot vegetable casserole
directions: Place 1/2 the soup and 1/2 the Cheez Whiz in the bottom of the crock-pot.
Add frozen vegetables and mushrooms.
Top with remaining soup and cheese.
Cook on low for 7 hours.

title: french onion casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook onions and butter.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Add bouillon and wine.
Stir until thick and bubbly.
Pour in 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with croutons, Swiss and Parmesan cheese. Brown under broiler just until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: alabama sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Turn into a plate lined with pastry.
Bake in a hot oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate; bake for 25 to 35 minutes longer, or until pie is set.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze to remove moisture.
Saute onion in oil.
Add spinach and cook until excess moisture is evaporated. Let cool.
Beat eggs in bowl and add cheese.
Stir into spinach mixture.
Pour into greased quiche pan or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix
and
sift
flour,
sugar,
baking powder and salt. Stir in coconut.
Combine milk, egg, butter and vanilla.
Stir in well. Add
dates, apples and pecans; mix well.
Spoon into 2 greased and
floured
loaf
pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: "miss jessie's" vidalia onions and cucumbers
directions: Layer cucumbers and onions in
large bowl.
Salt as you layer, cover and refrigerate for
hours.
Blend
sugar	and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers and onions (that have been drained after 6 hours of refrigeration). Deliciously crunchy.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potato wedges, peel sides down, in shallow baking dish, 9 x 13-inch pan or 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Mix oil, cheese, salt, garlic powder, paprika and pepper; brush over all the potatoes.
Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and golden, brushing occasionally with oil mixture.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers and remove stem from tops and then chop up the tops.
Parboil peppers for 5 minutes. Brown meat. Add chopped pepper tops and onion. Add tomatoes. Add Worcestershire sauce and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Thicken with bread crumbs. Stuff peppers and put in covered dish with some water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and oil; beat well.
Add nuts and zucchini and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with 10x sugar (powdered).
Keep in fridge until eaten.

title: german potato salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, add chopped onion.
Fry bacon, remove bacon.
Add butter and flour to bacon fat.
Stir and add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Boil and pour over potatoes, then sprinkle bacon over salad.

title: little pecan pies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Pat firmly, with no gaps, into smallest cupcake tins, well greased.
Mix remaining ingredients. Fill your little patted "nests" with this mixture and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Drain and dice peaches and pineapple.
Add bananas and strawberries.
Combine all fruit in large bowl.
Bring water to a boil; add sugar and boil until clear.
Pour over fruit.
Line muffin tins with cupcake liners.
Fill with fruit mixture and freeze overnight.
Set out 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix drained fruits together.
Add buttermilk; mix well. Sprinkle instant pudding; mix again.
Add Cool Whip.

title: broccoli-noodle stir-fry
directions: Break noodles into pieces.
Reserve seasoning packet.
Place noodles in 1-quart microsafe casserole.
Add warm water.
Cook on high 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until noodles are softened, stirring twice.
Drain.

title: creamy caramels
directions: Combine sugar, salt and corn syrup in large heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cook to firm ball stage (245° on candy thermometer), stirring occasionally.
Add butter and cream gradually so that mixture continues to boil.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture returns to 245°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
Cool; turn onto waxed paper.
Cut into 3/4 inch squares. Wrap squares in waxed paper.

title: everyday casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper together in heavy skillet.
Cook noodles, then add to meat mixture.
Add 1 can cream-style corn and 2 cans of chicken noodle soup.
Simmer together for 15 minutes.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cracker and melted butter combination.
Casserole can be frozen at this point.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pepperoni quiche
directions: Place frozen pie in oven and bake 3 minutes at 400°.
Prick shell and bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill pie crust with strawberries.
To prepare glaze, mix water, sugar, cornstarch and cook over medium heat until clear. Add strawberry jello.
Pour over strawberries.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with strawberries.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients except marshmallow cream.
Pour mixture into long pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool 15 minutes.
While cake is still warm, spread the marshmallow cream on top.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add brown sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture.
Add pineapple, walnuts and raisins.
Drop by spoonful on greased pan and bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and squash in a little oil until onion is just translucent; cover and let steam for a few minutes.
Mix squash, onion, carrots, sour cream and mushroom soup.
Melt butter and toss with stuffing.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix muffin mix and milk.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable beef barley soup
directions: Add all ingredients, except barley to 2 quarts water.
Cover and cook about 2 hours.
Add barley; cook 1 more hour.
Remove meat, shred and return to soup.
Serve.

title: bologna stack
directions: Mix cream cheese and seasonings together well.
Spread between layers of bologna to make a stack.
Place whole stack on serving dish.
Can be garnished with broccoli flowerets, etc.
Serve with crackers large enough to accomodate a slice from the stack.

title: creamed lettuce
directions: Whip milk; stir in sugar and vinegar.
Add lettuce and sliced eggs.
Serve.

title: "crazy" chocolate pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients in large flat cake pan.
Make 3 wells in mixture.
Put oil in one, vinegar in another and vanilla in the third.
Then pour water over all.
Mix ingredients then beat well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 75 biscuits.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until done.
Combine broccoli and soup with hamburger and place in pie crust.
Add shredded cheese on top and place the other crust on top of all.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with cheese and place in baking dish.
Mix crackers and melted margarine.
Place over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown and crunchy.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour into mixing bowl.
Bring to a rapid boil the butter, shortening, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour-sugar mixture and mix well.

title: frozen cranberry fruit round
directions: Combine ingredients, reserving cranberry and pineapple cans. Lightly grease cans and spoon salad mixture into cans.
Cover tightly with foil and freeze overnight.
Slice before serving.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour into large covered container.
Store in the refrigerator up to 6 months.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and chop.
Sprinkle cheese on hot potatoes.
Add onion, green pepper, crumbled bacon, egg and salt.
Pour 2 tablespoon hot bacon grease on top of potato mixture and toss. Then mix vinegar, water, mustard, mayonnaise and sugar together; pour on potato mixture and toss again.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a casserole dish or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: hobo bread
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Set aside in a large bowl to cool. Preheat the oven to 350°.
When date mixture is cool, add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together well. Fill well-greased pans 3/4 full. This can be baked in soup cans.
Bake for 1 hour.
I use the small loaf pans and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
This is a large recipe!

title: sweet berry bread
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
In a medium bowl cream together butter, sugar and almond extract.
Add eggs, one at a time,
beating thoroughly after each. Add flour mixture and berries mixing only until blended.
Grease an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan then line with wax paper and grease the paper.
Turn batter into pan smoothing top evenly with spoon. Bake at 325° from 50 to 60 minutes or until pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Let bread stand in pan on cake rack for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.
Peel off paper and turn bread right side up to cool completely.
When cool, wrap airtight and let bread stand for one day before slicing.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: In large bowl combine carrots, marshmallows, raisins, celery and nuts.
Add salad dressing; toss lightly.
Cover and chill. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crust:
Cream margarine and flour; add nuts.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In a large bowl cream together sugar and butter, till light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and add to the creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, add vanilla.

title: reese bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add confectioners sugar a little at a time (you may not need it all). Spread in a buttered 9 x 13 pan. Put last 2 ingredients in a bowl and microwave until melted. Spread over peanut butter mixture. Let set, then cut into squares.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup pecans. Form into ball and roll ball in reserved nuts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put first 2 ingredients in food chopper and add nutmeats and sugar.
Mix together and let set overnight before serving.

title: company casserole
directions: Mix everything, except corn flakes and oleo.
Place in casserole pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cook peas using package directions; drain.
Cool.
Layer lettuce, green onion, celery and peas in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Spread with mixture of sour cream and mayo.
Top with crumbled cheese and bacon.
Chill, covered, until serving time.

title: cous-cous and vegetables
directions: Chop the vegetables and mix with olive oil, cumin and cinnamon.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roast uncovered in 400° oven for 45 minutes, stirring 3 or 4 times during cooking.
In the last 5 minutes of cooking, add the frozen peas and stir well.

title: red velvet party cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to sugar mixture.
Sift flour and salt; add flour and buttermilk to sugar mixture.
Beat.
Combine vinegar and soda; add to batter (fold in). Pour into four 8 1/4 x 8 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch heart-shaped pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes; then remove from pan.
Spread frosting between each layer and top with frosting.

title: three layer jam cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, vanilla, jam and eggs.
Sift flour together with the other dry ingredients, then combine the two mixtures alternately with buttermilk.
Add raisins, nuts and coconut.
(Take out 1 1/2 cups batter and save.)
Pour remaining batter equally into 3 round cake pans and bake in your oven as you would any other heavy cake. After cake is cool, take the reserved batter and mix in
1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup milk.
Cook until thickened. Cool and spread in between layers and on top.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: sicilian salad
directions: In a large bowl chop all salad greens and other ingredients in small pieces.

title: cranberry swirl cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add baking soda, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Grease angel, tube or Bundt pan.
Put in 1/2 cake batter, then cranberry sauce, then nuts, then remaining cake batter and swirl with a knife.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: california vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package.
Parboil vegetables until almost cooked.
Stir cheese into hot vegetables and add mushroom soup.
Place vegetable mixture in baking dish.
Pat stuffing mix on top of vegetables.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and drizzle over stuffing.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Lightly spray a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 baking dish with Pam.
Place in a 9 x 13 filled with 1-inch of water.
Set aside.
Place bread cubes in the bottom of the smaller dish.
Put milk in a saucepan and heat to scalding.
Remove from the heat.
Add sugar, flour, salt, butter, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour over bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check after 45 minutes as ovens may vary.
Pudding is done when a knife inserted near the middle comes out clean.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: In skillet, bring 1 inch of water to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook just until pink (2 or 3 minutes).
Drain.
Cut shrimp into thirds and set aside.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Use juices from strawberries and pineapple and make Jell-O.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt 3 times.
Add to mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for about 2 hours with pan of water in bottom of oven.
(Makes cake moist.)

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in
order
given and bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and salt and add milk.
Cook until as thick as gravy.
Tastes best over hot homemade biscuits.

title: italian cream cake
directions: In large bowl, cream together sugar, margarine and shortening, then add 1 egg at a time, mixing after each egg.
Sift flour and soda together and add to mixture.
Add the buttermilk and mix well.
Stir in coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes.
Frost while still warm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind
cranberries
in food chopper.
Place sugar, salt and lemon
juice
over cranberries and let stand for 2 hours. Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add cold water and stir until dissolved.
When
Jell-O
is
syrupy,
add
cranberry mixture, celery, nuts and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until firm. This salad may also be frozen.
Yields 6 servings.

title: granola
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Combine oil and honey and pour over mixture.
Mix well until all is coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Prepare marinara sauce.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta shells according to label.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Fill each shell with mix (about 1 tablespoon per shell) and place in baking dish lined with sauce.
Pour sauce over shells.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate cream pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk 1 cup at a time.
Beat egg yolks well and add to mixture.
Cook in double boiler until thick, then add 1/4 stick margarine and vanilla.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch already baked pie crust.
Makes 2 pies.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a medium size bowl, stir together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell and bake for 1 hour.

title: tim's fancy fast chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Top each piece with slice of Swiss cheese. Top with mushrooms. Mix can of soup with wine and pour over chicken. Spread stuffing mix over top and drizzle melted butter over top. Bake 1 hour at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain tuna and cut up.
Peel and shred carrot.
Cut celery into small pieces.
In large bowl, gently mix cooked macaroni, tuna, carrot and celery.
Mix in mayonnaise, and salt and pepper to taste.

title: beans with apples and sausage
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring to break into chunks. Remove meat.
Pour off excess grease if any.
Saute apples and onions in sausage grease until browned.
Add sausage and sugar; cover and continue cooking until tender.
Add beans; stir, heat and serve.
Can also be heated in a crock-pot or casserole. Serves 4.

title: betty's pancakes
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Add egg, buttermilk and melted margarine. Do not overbeat.

title: easy fruitcake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In medium bowl, combine dates, cherries, pineapple, raisins, and pecans.

Mix well. In large bowl, combine the pie crust mix, baking soda, sugar and spices. Stir to mix. Add the eggs and beat well. Stir in the fruit mixture. Mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing the cookies about 2 inches apart. Bake for about 10 minutes, until light brown. Remove from the cookie sheet and place on a rack to cool completely before storing. Be careful as you remove the cookies from the cookie sheet because they are fragile while hot. They become more crispy as they cool. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook in large pot the sliced squash, onion and green pepper in salted water until tender.
Drain off liquid but save.
Put 1/2 cup of liquid in a buttered casserole dish.
Beat eggs and mix with shredded cheese.
Pour over top of squash.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over squash.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup to hot rice. Mix all together and put into a greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chopped egg salad tea sandwiches
directions: On a large wooden cutting board, crush garlic.
Discard clove, leaving the juice on the board.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan; bring to a boil. Boil on medium heat for 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until it melts.
Beat in Marshmallow Creme.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone.
Beat eggs and other ingredients, in order given.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan until brown.

title: lemon roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Add ReaLemon, bouillon and Tabasco sauce; set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine cooked rice, broccoli, cheese and 1/4 cup of lemon butter sauce.
Mix well.
Divide rice mixture for 8 fillets, rolling each.
Place seam side down in baking dish.
Brush with remaining lemon butter sauce.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers to about 1/4-inch thick.
Beat together the eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip the cucumber in the egg mixture then in the bread crumbs.
Fry a few slices at a time in the butter in a large skillet until light brown.
Drain well and serve while still hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water. Add other ingredients until well mixed. Put in freeze 1 day before using. Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving. In punch bowl, add two liter of ginger ale.

title: marinated fajitas
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and marinate steak overnight. Grill steak, cut in thin strips across the grain of the meat. Serve with warm flour tortillas, picante sauce, guacamole, chopped tomatoes, sour cream, etc.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs and chocolate syrup. Mix together thoroughly. Mix dry ingredients and add to chocolate mixture. Stir in chopped nuts. Bake in greased jellyroll pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemony gingerbread
directions: Mix and bake gingerbread according to directions.
While gingerbread is baking, prepare lemon sauce.
Mix lemon juice to taste with margarine and confectioners sugar until you have about 2 cups of sauce.
It is up to you how sweet or tart sauce is.
When gingerbread is done, remove from oven and take fork and poke holes in cake.
Pour lemon sauce over gingerbread and cover for a short time.
Lemon sauce goes into gingerbread.
Is best served warm.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Choose 5 green peppers of uniform size and which will stand upright.
Cut slice from stem end and scoop out seeds and membranes.
Parboil about 2 minutes in boiling water; drain thoroughly.
Stuff with this mixture:
Saute onion and tomato in butter until onion is slightly soft.
Add corn, salt and ground beef and heat to bubbling.
Stuff mixture into peppers and top with bread crumbs.
Place peppers in a buttered shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° until crumbs are toasted and stuffing is hot, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, butter, milk, sugar and egg yolks.
Mix well. If mixture is too dry, add more milk.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Pour
pudding mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Top with meringue made with egg whites. Yields 8 servings.

title: cucumber sour cream dressing
directions: In a bowl, blend together vinegar, sugar and salt. Fold in sour cream and cucumbers. Serve immediately over sliced beets or sliced tomatoes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin in thin narrow strips.
Cook in butter with onions until meat is brown.
Reduce heat and add mushrooms.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Remove meat and vegetables to double boiler.
To remaining broth, add flour and seasoning gradually.
Add sour cream.
Blend until smooth.
Add meat and vegetables from double boiler and serve on bed of noodles or rice.

title: crunchy party chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips.
Sprinkle chips on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Mix salt and cabbage.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze excess moisture from cabbage.
Add carrots and green pepper.
Mix together in saucepan remaining ingredients.
Boil 1 minute. Cool, then pour over cabbage.
Mix well and serve.
May be put in containers and frozen.

title: beet pickles
directions: Heat this mixture very hot.
Wash fresh, cleaned beets with peel on and cut tops off, leaving about 1 1/2-inch tops on.
Cook with water until tender, but not too done.
Cool and peel beets, placing them into a clean bowl.
Place them into liquid and heat. Add 3 or 4 whole cloves into hot, clean jars and 1 stick cinnamon, also.
Seal with new jar lids.
Makes approximately 2 quarts and 1 pint.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, oil and pumpkin pie mix.
Cream together.
Add remaining ingredients; beat 2 minutes with mixer. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and one loaf pan or 3 loaf pans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Boil mayo, sugar, vinegar and oil.
Mix well and let cool.
Pour over vegetables and chill.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Chop one medium-size onion and brown in small amount of olive oil
Drain onions and remove from skillet.
Brown 1 1/2 pounds hamburger, drain and set aside.
Mix together 1 cup flour, 1 tsp. salt, 1 tsp. oregano, 1/8 tsp. pepper, 1/4 tsp. basil,
1/4 tsp. garlic powder, 2 eggs and 2/3 cup milk. Pour mixture into greased and floured pizza pan.
Spread hamburger and onions over batter. Spread one jar pizza sauce over hamburger mixture; add mushroom pieces if desired.
Bake at 425 degrees for 30-40 minutes.
Add cheese the last 5 minutes of baking.
6 servings.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add alternately to sugar mixture with milk and mashed bananas.
Mix well.
Add nuts and bake in two 8-inch layer cake pans at 350° until done.

title: carrot salad
directions: Stir all ingredients into a bowl.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *Ritz crackers are the best, but any kind are okay (just enough to cover the casserole).

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In medium bowl mix on low speed the cream cheese until fluffy. Mix in the sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: white chili
directions: In a pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add finely chopped onion; saute until brown.
In a large stockpot, add onions and next 7 ingredients; stir until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chopped chicken into the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add chicken and rice soup, cream of chicken soup and milk.
Stir together, leaving chicken on bottom.
Put chow mein noodles on top and it's ready for the oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine mushroom soup and beef.
Mix all ingredients together and top with Cheddar cheese soup.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Add water to egg white and beat until frothy. Add egg white mixture to pecans and stir until well coated.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon; sprinkle over pecans while stirring until the pecans are well coated.
Place coated pecans in a large, well-greased shallow pan. Dot generously with butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sausage and lentil stew
directions: Put water and bouillon cubes in a 4-quart Dutch oven and bring to a boil over high heat.
While liquid comes to a boil, prepare and add all the remaining ingredients in order given.
Let contents of pot boil very briskly for about 30 seconds while you stir the mixture constantly.

title: russian corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Cream together the first five ingredients.
Fold in 1 cup grated hot or mild Mexican Velveeta cheese.
Spread mixture onto flour tortillas.
Roll up tightly and refrigerate overnight. Slice into pinwheels.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: beer bread
directions: Blend altogether.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken for two
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Use a 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Melt shortening in pan.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in bag.
Shake chicken in bag, 2 to 3 pieces at a time. Place chicken skin down in pan.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes; turn. Bake until tender, 18 to 20 minutes longer.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix eggs and cake mix.
Add sugar, water and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in sour cream.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and beat in.
When blended add shortening and beat.
Cut apples into crosswise slices (core but don't peel).
Dip into batter.
Drop into hot fat and fry at 375° until brown.
Drain and serve hot.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Layer cooked spaghetti, "torn" American cheese (3 to 4 slices), 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, 1/2 can tomato sauce and 1/2 of each seasoning.
Repeat the layers. Top with can of whole tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with Parmesan cheese to serve. Serve with green salad and choice of yellow vegetable.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, carrot, pimento, soup and sour cream.
In a casserole dish, spread a layer of stuffing and butter, a layer of squash mixture, then another layer of stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter or margarine, oil and sugars in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat for 1 minute until well blended.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat well.
In separate bowl combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
About 5 dozen cookies.
Really good!

title: heaven and earth
directions: Cook potatoes in 1 cup boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt in a large covered pan until almost tender.
Stir in apples.
Continue cooking over low heat, stirring occasionally, until apples are tender and crisp. Fry bacon until crisp. Remove from skillet and crumble into bits; keep warm.
Fry onions in bacon fat until light brown.
Keep warm.
Mash apple-potato mixture with a large spoon, leaving in large lumps. Toss with half of the bacon and onion. Place in serving dish and sprinkle the remaining bacon and onions. Keep warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: roasted pecan clusters
directions: Melt butter, pour in 15 x 10 x 1-inch
jelly
roll pan. Add pecans and stir to coat.
Bake in 300°
oven
for
25 minutes, stirring
every
10 minutes.
Put on
paper
towel
and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Place candy coating
in
top
of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil, reduce heat
to low and cook until coating melts.
Cool 2 minutes, add pecans and stir until
coated. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed
paper
and
let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and 1/2 of the beef in a bowl.
Mix should be shaped into two small balls or 1 large.
Roll in remaining beef which has been ground in food processor or cut in small pieces.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add vegetables and soup.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas cookies
directions: Line pan with butter (8 x 8-inch pan for regular recipe and 9 x 12-inch pan for 1 1/2 recipes).
Cover with whole graham crackers. Melt 2 sticks oleo.
Mix egg, milk and sugar together; add to melted oleo.
Bring to boil.
(Stir constantly to prevent burning.) Remove from heat; add nuts, coconut and crumbs.
Pour over the layer of graham crackers in the pan.
Top with whole graham crackers.
Pour icing over the mixture.
Chill 5 hours.
Freezes very well.
Make it the day before or make it ahead and freeze to use later.

title: italian calzones
directions: Filling:
In skillet, brown ground beef, sausage and mushrooms.
Drain.
Stir in 1/2 jar pizza quick and pepperoni. Set aside.

title: tuna layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients, starting with lettuce and ending with salad dressing on top.

title: cheddar-rice patties
directions: Combine rice, cheese, onion, flour, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in small bowl until stiff but not dry.
Fold beaten egg whites into rice mixture.
Coat large skillet with vegetable cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons batter into skillet for each patty; push batter into diamond shape using spatula.
Cook patties, turning once, until golden brown on both sides.
Serve warm with applesauce, apple wedges or sour cream.
Makes about 1 dozen (4 servings).

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain and squeeze dry.
Mix with other ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda; let cool.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured pan and bake at 350°.

title: cheddar baked potatoes
directions: In a small bowl combine soup, paprika and pepper.
In greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes in overlapping rows. Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon soup mix over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients, except pecans. When mixed good, add pecans.
Pour into crust and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy delicious pickles
directions: Drain pickles and discard vinegar. Slice pickles and return to jar. Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil and pour over pickles.

title: microwave savory ribs and sauerkraut
directions: In 3-quart casserole, cook onion, green pepper and oil (covered) on High, stirring once.
Add paprika and cook 1 more minute.
Stir in undrained sauerkraut, tomato sauce, brown sugar, bouillon and caraway seed.
Tuck in pork chops.
Cook, covered, on High for 35 to 40 minutes or until meat is fork-tender, turning ribs over and rearranging after 15 minutes.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
In a separate saucepan, heat soup, milk, green chilies and cheese until the cheese is melted.
Layer a 9 x 13 pan with the tortilla shells. Rip the shells into small pieces and cover the bottom of the pan. Sprinkle half of the hamburger on top of the shells.
Pour half of the sauce over the hamburger.
Repeat tortillas, hamburger and sauce one more time.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: egg song
directions: For perfect soft-boiled eggs, sing "Onward Christian Soldiers" once; for medium boiled eggs, sing twice.
For hard-boiled, sing three times.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix well, but don't knead.
Cover and let rise about 8 hours. It should double in size.
After rising, punch down.
Separate into 3 parts.
Put in a little flour on countertop and knead dough a few times to get out bubbles.
Put in loaf pans that have been sprayed with oil.
Spray lightly the top of the loaves.
Let rise 8 hours or until double in size.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, until top crust is brown.
Take out of pans soon after baking and place on a paper towel to cool.
This can also be used to make rolls.
Bake in sprayed muffin tins, for less time, same temperature.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and salt.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Bake 1 hour or more until thick at 350°.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Stir in milk; mix well.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with water.
Add to egg mixture.
Cook over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken; add vanilla.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir in custard. Add whipped cream and marshmallows.
Chill and serve with coconut cake.

title: never fail pie crust(this is an old and good recipe for pie crust.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together well.
Separate into two balls and roll dough on floured surface.
Ready for pie plate!

title: peach brandy
directions: Open the shucks of corn carefully and leave the husks (green part) attached.
Remove all of the corn silk with your hands, then remove the remaining silk with a vegetable brush.
Wash the corn and shucks with water.
Do not dry.
Pull the shucks back up around the ear of each corn cob and twist the top ends to hold in place.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with crisp, raw vegetables.

title: meatball kabobs
directions: Combine ingredients except oil and cumin.
Use 1 teaspoon cumin (save rest); mix well.
Shape into meatballs.
In small bowl, mix oil and remaining cumin.
Put meatballs on skewers with onions and peppers.
Brush with oil mixture.
Grill over hot coals, rotating until done.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Strain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients in a large pot.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours; then simmer about 2 hours.
Add 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese and serve hot over spaghetti.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add berries, stirring until dissolved.
Pour juice from pineapple in another bowl.
Add softened cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Set aside.
Add pineapple and nuts to berry mixture.
Pour 1/2 in a pan and chill. Remove from refrigerator and spread cheese mixture evenly.
Pour other 1/2 of berry mixture on top and chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle dry dressing to boned chicken and mix with fork to coat.
Add green pepper, chopped.
Cook rice until half done.
Put in casserole.
Pour chicken mixture over rice, spreading evenly. Pour tomatoes as desired over chicken.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and pepper is done to taste.

title: whip frosting
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Will ice 1/2 sheet cake.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt and sprinkle over peaches.
Sprinkle lemon juice and extract over peaches and dot with butter.
Put in preheated hot oven (400°) until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix up Bisquick using shortcake recipe on box.
Remove hot bubbly peaches from oven and drop shortcake mix onto hot peaches, covering top, not solid.
Put back in oven about 20 minutes more until shortcake is done.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin; mix well.
Cool. Add cheese, mayo, grated onion, cucumber and nuts. Pour into a wet mold and refrigerate.

title: bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie pan (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center and edges comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: pink punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all ingredients, except ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale.

title: shrimp etouffees
directions: Saute the first 7 ingredients.
Add soup and salt.
Heat and stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until shrimp are done. Serve over rice.

title: beef stroganoff(makes 3 cups)
directions: Slice mushrooms and onions.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Saute mushrooms and onions until soft.
Remove from skillet and set aside in large bowl.

title: orange frost
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ice, together in blender.
Add a few ice cubes at a time, beating at high speed until all ice cubes have been crushed.
Garnish with sprigs of mint and serve immediately.

title: rum sauce
directions: Bring to boil in medium saucepan the water and oleo.
Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
Add oleo mixture.
Add vanilla, butter and rum flavorings.
Cook until it bubbles.
Serve hot over bread pudding.

title: chestnut dressing
directions: Boil veal steaks until cooked, then cut in small pieces.
Brown onion, meat, almonds, chestnuts, raisins, tomato paste and rice. Cook until rice is tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool, then stuff turkey.
This dressing will stuff a 20-pound turkey.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Prepare apples and put in pan.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Pour batter over apples.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut off top of tomato.
Carefully remove pulp of tomato, leaving solid shell.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Fill tomatoes with mixture and chill.

title: tangy brown ribs
directions: Place meat in baking dish, brush with Wesson Oil, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Drain fat. Combine onion, vinegar, sugar and mustard and spread on meat. Pour on Hunt's sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done, basting occasionally with sauce.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
While fettuccine cooks, heat butter and cream in a small saucepan until butter melts over low heat.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Keep warm over low heat.
Drain fettucine; pour into bowl. Pour sauce over noodles.
Toss until noodles are coated.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, dessert topping mix and cold milk.
Spread half of crumb mixture in an oblong baking dish. Add half of cream cheese mixture.
Spread on cherry pie filling. Add remaining cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: rocky road pizza
directions: Beat butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and flour.
Spread in ungreased pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top with pecans, miniature marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes more.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Have turkey sliced in deli (1 pound makes 10 to 12 slices). Cook stuffing according to directions.
Roll in log form; wrap with turkey slices.
Place in baking dish.

title: pasta and pesto
directions: Melt butter and combine with all ingredients, except Parmesan, in a small saucepan and warm.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over hot pasta noodles and spoon on pesto sauce (a little goes a long way). This goes well with the Cajun Broiled Chicken.
It's also very good if boiled shrimp is mixed in with the pasta.
Fast and easy.

title: chicken pie casserole
directions: Place chicken and vegetables in a greased, shallow, 2-quart dish.
Mix broth and soup together; add pepper.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Stew the chicken and breasts and pull off the bones.
In a large pot, cook the bell pepper and onion in margarine until onion is clear and pepper is tender.
Drain mushrooms and add to pepper/onion mixture. Boil the spaghetti in chicken broth. When tender, drain and add to pepper/onion/mushroom mixture. Add chicken, peas and pimentos.
Add cheese.
Melt slowly.
Cook until all is blended.
Makes a big amount.

title: jody's cheese dip
directions: *Jar of cheese and salsa should be the same size.

title: first graders
directions: Add all of the ingredients gently into a cheerful kindergarten room.
Mix for 2 1/2 hours from September until June.
Remove carefully for 3 sunny summer months.
Add
a dash of hugs and kisses daily.

title: brown bread
directions: Cook raisins and water 10 minutes and cool (slowly so water doesn't evaporate).
Mix together flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix all wet ingredients, then add dry.
Cut lids from 4 (Number 2) vegetable cans.
Grease well, fill 2/3 full and place on baking sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Use bottom shelf in oven.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from cans.

title: yummy bars
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: no-peek pheasant
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Empty box of rice in bottom of pan and sprinkle seasoning packet over rice.
Mix mushroom and chicken soups with two cups water and pour evenly over the rice.
Arrange pieces of pheasant on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over birds.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stove top beef noodles
directions: Lightly brown beef in large skillet.
Drain fat off. Add remaining ingredients except noodles and Parmesan cheese.
Cook, covered, slowly for about 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Add noodles and stir well.
Add a little more water, if needed.
Stir frequently until most of the liquid is absorbed and noodles are cooked. Serve hot with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.

title: rabbit sausage
directions: Grind rabbit meat.
Add all ingredients, mixing well.
Make into patties.
Ready to fry.
Cook until well done.
Can be frozen for special occasions.

title: quick cocoa cake(one bowl)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift first 6 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add the rest of ingredients, but do not stir until everything is in.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 40 minutes.
Drop 1 cup chocolate chips on top of cake before putting in oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after baking in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party snack
directions: Hollow bread out so that it makes a bowl.
Cube the bread from the inside.
Mix soup with mayonnaise and sour cream.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Fill bread bowl with the dip mixture and arrange cubed bread around outside of "bowl."
Dip cubes and when you are finished you may eat the bowl!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, celery, onions, pimientos and Wesson oil.
Put in covered bowl.
Put sugar over top of this mixture.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Stir next morning.

title: nectarine cream pie
directions: Cook together until thickened strawberries, cornstarch and lemon juice; cool.
Blend cream cheese with powdered sugar; stir in whipped cream.
Spread in bottom of cooled pie shell.
Place sliced nectarines on top of base in pie shell.
Top with cooled, cooked strawberry topping.
Chill before serving.

title: hearty bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour in ungreased 2-quart casserole dish; cover.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: texas brisket
directions: Mix the ingredients, except coffee, the night before; put in the refrigerator.
Pour 1 cup of strong coffee over large brisket. Cover with foil and cook at 250° overnight (or at least 8 to 9 hours).

title: wassail
directions: Add all in large pot.
Simmer for at least one hour before serving.

title: quick chic trick
directions: Tear up chicken and place in bottom of a greased baking dish. Heat soup and the sour cream.
Add seasonings and pour over chicken.
(You can thin with a little water or broth.)
Crush crackers over top; then drizzle with melted oleo.
(If using egg noodles, layer them directly over the chicken.)
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
(Water chestnuts are also good in this dish.)

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix ingredients. Microwave 4 minutes. Serve with nachos.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add flour and chips. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Press hole in center. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: russian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in dish.
Mix onion soup, Russian dressing and apricot preserves.
Pour over chicken.
Cook in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry sherbet
directions: Boil cranberries with water until cranberries pop and are soft. Sieve cranberries. Add sugar and juice.
Freeze, stirring occasionally.
Great with Thanksgiving dinner.

title: cheese cake(no cooking)
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water. Chill until slightly thick. Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin and blend well. Fold in whipped condensed milk.
Mix the crackers and oleo together.
Put 2/3 in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Add filling and sprinkle rest of crumbs over top. Chill several hours or overnight. Serves 12 to 16.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and squares of milk chocolate.
Sift cake flour, salt and soda.
Alternate sifted mixture and buttermilk to creamed sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in round pan or 325° oven for 45 minutes in a square pan.

title: broccoli with herb butter
directions: Trim heavy, coarse stalks from broccoli. Steam broccoli spears for 20 minutes or until tender. Combine and heat remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli. Serves 6.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Set a heavy zip-lock bag in a large mixing bowl and place the chicken in the bag. Add the chicken broth, oil, vinegar, basil, oregano or tarragon, onion powder and garlic. Close bag and turn to coat chicken well. Marinate for 5-24 hours in the refrigerator, turning occasionally. Drain the chicken, reserving the marinade. Place the chicken on an unheated rack in a broiler pan. Brush with the marinade. Broil 4-5 inches from heat for 20 minutes or until lightly browned, brushing often with the marinade. Turn chicken and broil for 5-15 minutes more, until chicken is tender and no longer pink. This has 1 gram carbohydrate.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream the lard with sugar until fluffy.
Blend in the almond extract.
Thoroughly mix in the flour, one cup at a time.
The last addition makes the mixture crumbly.
To shape each cookie, measure 1 level teaspoon of dough and press with your hands to form a flat, round cake about 1 3/4-inches in diameter.
Place cookies on greased baking sheet, slightly apart (they do not spread).
Gently press an almond in center of each cookie.
Combine egg yolk with water and brush the mixture over the cookies.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 30 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: diabetic oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Chill dough; it turns out better cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° until topping is brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in heavy saucepan, add milk and cook slowly, stirring constantly.
When mixture is hot, add egg yolks and continue cooking until thick; add butter and vanilla. Pour in baked pie shell and cover with meringue, bake at 350° until brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and put in jars with 1 slice onion, 1 dill head, 1 garlic bud and small piece of alum (to a jar).
Boil other ingredients and pour over pickles and seal.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly (time from when mixture starts to bubble around edges of pan).
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir for 1 minute, until marshmallows melt and blend. Pour into 8-inch buttered square pan.
Cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make sauce by combining Miracle Whip, red wine vinegar and sugar.
Chill and refrigerate 2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over and mix; chill and serve.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Broil chicken at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken; continue to broil 5 to 10 more minutes.
Cook bacon; drain on paper towel.
Break in half.
Add 3 pieces of bacon on top of chicken.
Put slice of cheese over bacon and melt under broiler.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in 3-quart casserole dish. Cover with 2 cups crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shish kabob(microwave)
directions: Make marinade by combining vinegar, oil, onion salt, garlic, soy sauce, oregano and water in large bowl.
Cut meat in 1-inch cubes.
Add to marinade and let stand refrigerated 5 to 6 hours. Stir occasionally.
Arrange meat cubes and vegetables alternately on 6 long wooden skewers.
Place 2 or 3 skewers at a time on microproof dinner plate.
Cook uncovered on High (maximum power) 1 to 1 1/2 minutes for medium rare.
Repeat for remaining skewers. Cook slightly longer for well-done meat.
(Total cooking time is 2 to 4 1/2 minutes.)

title: kare's toffee
directions: Melt butter and sugar in a pot, then add water and Karo syrup. Cook over low heat until mixture reaches hard-crack stage (300° if using candy thermometer).
Stir the whole time.
Remove from heat; add almonds and stir.
Spread toffee on 2 well-greased cookie sheets and cool.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar and 1/2 stick (4 tablespoons) butter; melt, stirring to combine.
Spread on bottom of cake pan (9-inch round x 3-inches deep).
Arrange peaches over brown sugar in concentric circles.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, beat remaining 1 1/2 sticks butter with sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg yolks.
Alternately beat in flour mixture with milk and vanilla until well blended.
In small bowl, beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Spread over peach slices.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°, or until a cake tester comes out dry.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Turn cake onto plate.
(Garnish with blueberries, optional.)
Can also be made in a 9-inch spring-form or 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: chicken wings oriental
directions: Fry wings in fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove lid and increase heat until liquid is almost gone.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix milk, sugar and flour together.
Pour flour mixture on top of butter.
Top with fruit (juice and all) or pie filling.
May sprinkle with a little cinnamon if desired.
Crust will rise to the top.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat both sides of tortilla shell with picante sauce while adding a little extra to the middle of one side. Add meat and cheese. Roll tightly and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam. Spread excess meat, cheese and sauce over top. Bake, uncovered, for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: a berry good banana smoothie
directions: Peel and slice bananas. Wash and cut off tops of strawberries (if you're using fresh).
Put into blender with milk and yogurt and whirl away.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients
and shape into meatballs.	Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 45 minutes, turning once.

title: macaroni and spinach cheese bake *
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; place in casserole and bake at 350° in preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, lime juice, onion, garlic, pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and marinade at least 1 hour at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator. Light charcoal grill or preheat broiler.
Remove chicken from marinade; reserve marinade.
Grill over medium-hot coals or broil, turning and basting with marinade several times, for 10 minutes or until chicken is opaque throughout, but still juicy.
Cut chicken into strips.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In oblong baking dish, combine soup, water, rice, mushrooms and 1/2 can onions.
Arrange chicken on rice mixture; sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken juices run clear.
Top with remaining onions for 5 more minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add flour and sugar.
Add the last 4 ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Stir-fry pork in hot oil until brown; remove from pan.
Add vegetables and cook, covered, 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend together soy sauce and cornstarch and add to the vegetables and the pork.
Cook and stir until the mixture is thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.

title: spicy vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Chill thoroughly.
Serve as a dip for celery sticks, carrot sticks or other raw, crisp vegetables.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.
Serving Size: 2 tablespoons. Exchanges:
free.

title: italian-style pasta salad
directions: Break pasta in half.
Cook, drain and set aside.
Drain artichokes; chop artichoke hearts.
In a large bowl, combine cooked pasta, artichokes, broccoli, carrot, summer sausage and Mozzarella cheese.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine potatoes, carrot, celery, onion, water, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a boil (10 to 12 minutes). Cover and reduce heat to low.
Continue cooking until vegetables are crisply tender (20 to 22 minutes); do not drain.
Meanwhile, in 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly (1 minute). Stir in milk.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil (10 to 12 minutes).
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients until cheese is melted.
Stir cheese sauce into undrained, cooked vegetables.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through (5 to 6 minutes).
Yields 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over 1 quart of your favorite fruit.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: tuna mold
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into "Pammed" mold or form into ball and refrigerate 3 hours.
Serve with party pumpernickle bread, party rye or your favorite crackers.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together well.
Pour boiling water over this, stirring well.
Mix egg yolks, salt, juice, grated rind of lemon and butter to sugar and cornstarch mixture.
Boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: easy one-dish meal
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese soup, milk, rice and meat.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour evenly over first mixture. Bake 27 to 30 minutes until light brown.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy eggplant casserole
directions: Slice unpeeled eggplant, 1/2-inch thickness.
Brown in shortening.
Remove.
Saute beef until done.
In well-oiled casserole dish, place layer of eggplant slices, layer of meat, layer of onions and sprinkle with salt.
Repeat layering and spread undiluted soup over top of all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 35 to 40 minutes, at 350°.

title: brown bread without steaming
directions: Add this to dry ingredients.
Blend well and pour into 2 greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Test and turn out on rack to cool.

title: broccoli quiche(4 servings)
directions: Use part of margarine to grease 10-inch quiche pan.
Blend eggs, milk, margarine, flour, salt and pepper in blender.
Cook broccoli and drain.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix crackers and margarine and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine pudding and milk.
Beat on low setting until well blended. Fold in ice cream.
Pour over crust and top with whipped topping. Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: coconut slices
directions: Cream
sugar and shortening, salt and vanilla; add egg. Stir in
flour,
soda and coconut.
Shape in roll and freeze. Slice frozen
dough.
Cook on greased sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes. Yields 4 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare dressing according to package directions.
Spread 1/2 of dressing in an 8 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Add cut up chicken and mushrooms.
Spread over dressing and put remaining dressing on the top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in fat.
Stir in rice and water, bouillon cube and paste.
Add seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Stir well.
Cover.
Lower heat and simmer 25 minutes.
While still hot, put in cheese cubes and toss lightly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Blend together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Combine all and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into lightly greased casserole dish.

title: lola's red rice
directions: Saute vegetables in fat from bacon.
(May use olive oil and low-fat chopped ham, almost as good as bacon.)
Add tomato sauce, seasonings and bacon.
Pour over 2 cups uncooked rice into rice steamer and stir.
(Southern rice always better in a rice steamer.)
Cook 1 hour, stirring with a fork after 45 minutes. Adjust seasonings as needed.

title: chicken and pepper skillet
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices. Mix chicken, soy sauce, garlic powder, cornstarch and sugar; set aside.
Cut peppers into 1/4-inch strips.
Slice mushrooms.
Cook vegetables in 2 tablespoons hot oil in skillet for 2 minutes.
In same skillet after removing vegetables, in 3 more tablespoons of oil, cook chicken mixture, stirring quickly until tender (about 5 minutes).
Return vegetables to the skillet.
Add water and heat to boiling.
Serve with rice.

title: new year's eve beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: bean and sausage casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and brown in skillet. Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: onion dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup and sour cream.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least 2 hours.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables for dipping.
Makes 2 cups.

title: lentil soup with kielbasa
directions: In a large pot, bring chicken stock and water to a boil.
Add all other ingredients. Bring soup to a boil and continue boiling for 15 minutes. Simmer over low heat for at least 30 minutes. Freezes well.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix and blend. Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in oblong dish and freeze.
Take out of freezer 1 hour before serving.

title: cake pan mix
directions: In a blender, whip cottage cheese and a little lemon juice together until smooth.
Add salt and pepper and chives to taste. Each tablespoons contains only 10 to 15 calories.

title: italian bisquittes
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Add eggs, lemon flavoring and lemon rind.
Sift into mixture flour and baking powder.
Use enough flour to make dough stiff enough to roll into long thin rolls. Twist pieces into a twig shape.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar glaze if desired.

title: croissants
directions: Mix egg yolk with 1 tablespoon milk and set aside.
Cream margarine and 1/3 cup flour.
Roll between 2 sheets wax paper to a 12-inch rectangle.
Chill 1 hour.
Soften yeast in water.
Heat milk, sugar and salt until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Add 2 cups flour and 1 egg; stir in.
Stir in rest of flour.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll dough to 14-inch square. Place chilled margarine on half of dough.
