Fold over and seal. Roll 21 x 12-inch rectangle.
Seal edges and chill.
Fold in thirds, roll into 21 x 12-inch rectangle and chill.
Fold and chill twice more.
Fold in thirds to 12 x 7-inch.
Cut crosswise into fourths.
Roll to 12-inch circle.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Roll loosely.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes. Brush with yolk and milk mixture.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend the eggs, water and vinegar together and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients with shortening until consistency of cornmeal or small peas.
Make a hole in the center of the dry mixture and add the egg mixture.
Mix until it forms a ball.
Divide and roll out. Makes 2 (8 to 9-inch) pie crusts.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine water, yeast, salt and Crisco oil in large mixing bowl. Stir until well blended. Add flour. Mix well. Dough will be soft. Let rise until doubled in bulk. Punch down; roll into golf ball sized balls and place in greased pan. Let rise again until doubled. Bake in a 425° oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: hot or cold vegetable frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease a 9 x 13 baking dish. In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add zucchini, mushrooms, onions, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until tender. Remove from heat and let cool slightly.

title: beef casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in well-greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 5 minutes at 250°.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Combine and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken camomile
directions: Cook some spaghetti noodles in hot water until done.
Drain. Put spaghetti in a baking dish (6 noodles).
Grate Cheddar cheese. Put cheese on top of spaghetti.
Put into 325° oven for 5 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; remove bacon and grease.
Brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Stir everything together; put bacon on top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375° in Dutch oven.

title: pumpkin parfait
directions: *One and one-half teaspoons pumpkin pie spice can be used instead of these ingredients.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix this thoroughly, then place in saucepan and simmer slowly for 15 minutes.
This sauce can be prepared in larger quantity and kept in refrigerator until desired.
Amount to be used for basting can be removed and heated.
The sauce should be kept hot when used for basting.
This sauce is good for not burning when barbecuing.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Makes 2 cups.

title: vegetable cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vinegar in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over vegetables in jars. Refrigerate.
Will keep for 1 or 2 weeks.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Brown pork chops; pour off drippings.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; place onion and green pepper slices on each chop.
Pour soup and water over chops.
Cover; cook 45 minutes over low heat. Serve over rice.

title: pig eating cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Use wooden spoon end to punch holes in cake.
Mash cake flat with palm of hand.
Put pineapple juice and pineapple on top of cake.
Fix pudding as directed on box.
Soften cream cheese and blend with pudding. Pour on top of pineapple.
Then spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top of cake.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Keep cool.

title: coke jello mold
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries. Heat to a slow boil. Dissolve jello in juices. When cool to a syrupy consistency, add Coke, pineapple, cherries, chopped nuts and chopped cheese (little cubes). Congeal in mold.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix the ingredients well for 5 minutes at medium speed. Pour mixture into a well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Preheat deep fryer half full of oil.

title: swiss steak and mushroom gravy
directions: Cut round steak into serving size pieces and place in 5-quart crock-pot.	Place in layers with onion and season with salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom soup and milk in a bowl and spread evenly over top. Start crock-pot on high for about an hour, then turn to low for 7 to 8 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes and a salad. This is delicious.	(If you have a smaller crock-pot, just cut recipe in half.)

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a well-greased iron skillet or nonstick baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Tear baked cake into 3/4-inch pieces.
Prepare gelatin using 1 cup water.
When slightly thickened, stir in strawberries and yogurt.
Pour over angel food cake pieces.
Refrigerate.
Serve as a healthful dessert when it is set.

title: cocktail meatballs(or sausages)
directions: You will need 1 box of cocktail toothpicks.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine the first nine ingredients.
Mix well, then add tomatoes, peppers, onions and artichoke hearts.
Best if made day before.
Mix again.
Before serving, garnish with tomato slices and Parmesan cheese.

title: sugarless bars(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cook raisins, dates and apples in 1 cup water for 3 minutes. Stir in butter or margarine and cool.
Add sweetener, beaten eggs, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: grilled pork
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork in large bowl.
Place pork in bowl; cover and let stand at room temperature 1 hour or in refrigerator overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain and grill pork.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate pistachio bundt cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, eggs and water; blend well (2 minutes with electric mixer).
Pour 2/3 of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Add the chocolate syrup into remaining batter; mix well.
Pour over batter in pan; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Add and mix in order the sugar, shortening, eggs and bananas. Sift together the baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sicilian italian sausage
directions: For 4 to 6 servings, saute Italian sausage in olive oil until meat is no longer pink.
Add onions and garlic; saute until onions are soft.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, Veg-All and seasonings; simmer 15 minutes with sausage mixture.
Add red wine to tomato-sausage mixture and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together in a large container.
Store in an airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup mix for a small cup, 1/3 cup mix for a mug of cocoa.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits well in colander until all juice has run off (1 to 2 hours).
Prepare shallow casserole (8 x 12-inch) by greasing with margarine.
Add fruit.
Cover with mixture of brown sugar and curry powder.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and dot with margarine.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 12 or makes 2 quarts.

title: chipped beef gravy(fat-free)
directions: Tear beef into small pieces.
Place in colander and rinse to remove some of the salt.

title: chocolate nut brownies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla just until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into batter.
Fold in half the nuts.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brownies pull away from the sides of the pan. Cool on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: pan greaser
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer. Place in an airtight container and place in refrigerator. Use to coat cake pans before adding batter to keep from sticking.

title: curried chicken with apples(light)
directions: Heat oil in nonstick skillet.
Add chicken and salt and pepper.
Saute until browned - about 6 minutes.
Transfer to plate.
Add the apple, onion, ginger, and garlic to skillet.
Cook until apple and onion are tender - about 6 minutes.
Stir in curry powder; cook 1 minute.
Add chick, chutney, broth, half-and-half, and parsley; bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, until flavors are blended and the sauce thicken slightly, about 3 minutes. Sprinkle with almonds.
Serve over rice.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Mix chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Place in microwave for 3 minutes, stirring after every minute.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour into a greased glass dish and cool for 10 to 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Mix soy sauce and all following ingredients together. Marinate steaks all day.
Broil or grill steaks.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk, vanilla, slightly beaten egg yolks and butter.
Mix and cook until thick.
(Don't use a double boiler.)
Beat egg whites for meringue.
Add 1/4 cup of sugar to egg whites while beating.
Put in 350° oven and brown.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Arrange chicken in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drain sauerkraut; squeeze dry.
Spread over chicken.
Top with cheese; pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream cheese date and nut    sandwich filling
directions: Blend cream cheese and salt until soft and creamy. Add nuts and dates; mix well. Makes 1 3/4 quarts, enough for 35 regular sandwiches or 100 tea sandwiches.

title: unbaked fruitcake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the crumbs, dates, walnuts, pecans and raisins.
In a saucepan, melt the marshmallows, adding salt and, when cooled some, stir in the condensed milk.
Pour over the mixing bowl contents and mix well.
Shape into an oiled loaf pan (9 x 5 x 2-inch) and refrigerate for several hours.
May be topped with pecan halves or sliced candied cherries.
Cut into thin slices when serving.
May also be made in a tube pan or gelatin mold.

title: pineapple right-side-up cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup fluted tube pan. In	small saucepan, melt margarine;
stir in brown sugar until well
mixed.
Press
brown	sugar
mixture	in bottom of prepared pan.
Cut
pineapple
slices in half;
place 6 halves on top of the
brown	sugar.	Place
cherry in center of each pineapple half.
In large bowl, blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs at
low speed
until
moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into
prepared
pan.
Bake	40
to	50
minutes. Immediately invert onto cooling rack.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Bake at 325° for 15 or 20 minutes.
After baking, top with cherry pie filling.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes or until macaroni is done.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix well and roll in small balls.
In small bowl, mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Roll balls in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
well
and shape in square glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together, adding 1/2 cup water.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 65 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Add 1/2 cup raisins or 1/2 cup nuts, if desired.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Toss cheese and onion with flour.
(Use waxed paper and save a clean-up job.)
Spread chicken and peas on bottom of crust; sprinkle with cheese-onion mixture.
Combine and beat eggs, milk, garlic salt and pepper until well mixed (not frothy).
Pour over other ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until set and top is lightly browned.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread slices and butter one side.
Place in bottom of baking dish, buttered side down.
Cook sausage and drain.
Spoon over bread.
Salt and pepper according to taste. Blend eggs and half and half in blender. Pour over sausage.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover last 10 minutes.
Very good served for breakfast or brunch.

title: holiday onions
directions: Cook onions until almost tender.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
Add sugar.
When dissolved, add onions, a few at a time.
Brown lightly, turning to glaze evenly.
Remove to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan. Blend in flour.
Cook until it bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook one or two minutes, whisking constantly until smooth and thickened.
Pour sauce over the onions in the casserole dish.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in the skillet and add bread crumbs.
Brown lightly.
Sprinkle over onions.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scallops with mushrooms in shells
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt 1/4 cup of the butter in a small skillet and add the mushrooms.
Cook, stirring often, until the mushrooms are wilted and give up their liquid.
Add shallots and garlic.
Cook briefly.
Spoon the mushroom mixture into a mixing bowl.
Let cool briefly, then add 2 tablespoons of the remaining butter, the scallops, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper. Blend well.
Use the mixture to fill 6 seafood shells.

title: pikadillo and cornbread wedges
directions: Prepare cornbread; spray 8 x 1 1/2-inch nonstick round cake pan with cooking spray.
Stir together cornmeal, flour and baking powder in a medium bowl until well mixed.
Lightly beat egg whites in a small bowl.

Stir in buttermilk and oil until well combined. Pour the liquid ingredients all at once into the dry ingredients. Stir the mixture briskly with a fork until all the ingredients are just evenly moistened; do not overstir.
The batter will be lumpy. Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Turn out onto wire to cool slightly.

title: frosty cucumber mold
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water; cool.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream; mix well.
Chill until partially set. Fold in cucumbers, pimento and onion.
Pour into 1-quart mold. Chill until firm.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, reserving 1 cup tomato sauce.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Heat reserved tomato sauce and serve over meat loaf. Serves 6.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir peanuts, corn syrup, sugar and salt together in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes, uncovered.
Stir after 4 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla; stir and cook 2 minutes more. Stir in baking soda until light and foamy.
Pour on greased cookie sheet and cool 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Mix as usual.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Put bananas and oil in blender and liquify.
Add mixture and sugar to cake mix.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Combine 3 tablespoons brown sugar, 1/2 cup chopped nuts (pecans) and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour half the batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts, sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Stir in milk, brown sugar and oleo.
Add other ingredients (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Muffin cups need to be greased and floured.
Bake in 400° oven for 14 to 16 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Soak bread in milk and mash.
Add to other ingredients.
Make into patties and fry in butter.
Serve hot with lemon slices.

title: diet cookies
directions: Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 40 cookies; contains 20 calories each.

title: orange jupiter mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight jar.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend (do not overbeat). Add the almond and vanilla extracts.
Add flour; blend well.
Pour into greased and floured aluminum pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, eggs and milk thoroughly.
Form into a loaf.

title: pickled squash
directions: Put salt over veggies and water.
Let set 1 hour and drain. Combine vinegar, sugar and celery seed; boil 5 minutes.
Add veggies and cook 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Add melted butter. Mix in eggs and sugar, mixing well.
Add milk and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° until custard is set and brown.

title: party punch
directions: Mix everything together except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking dish combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and half the onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 8 1/2 cups or 10 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole and cook for approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Check after 45 minutes and if it is getting too thick, add some more water.

title: special green bean casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Add flour and cook until smooth.
Add cream slowly, then add cheese and seasonings.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: layered green salad
directions: Place lettuce (cut up) on bottom of glass 2-quart dish.
Next layer onion and uncooked thawed peas.
Layer eggs.
Top with Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle more cheese and Bac*Os on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Good.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine soup with water.
Measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture and add to ground beef.
Add bread crumbs, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into about 1-inch balls.
In a large skillet, brown meatballs in 1 tablespoon of shortening.
Add remaining soup mixture and 1 to 2 tablespoons of minced dill pickle (optional). Cover and cook over low heat, stirring now and then, or put in crock-pot and heat through.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a 9-inch square baking dish or a shallow 2 or 3-quart casserole dish, combine milk, rice, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg. Cover and bake in a 300° oven until thick and light golden in color (about 3 hours), or bake pudding, uncovered, and an amber, caramel flavored skin will form on top.
Serve pudding warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: troop 90 dutch oven peach cobbler
directions: You will also need charcoal and a 14-inch Dutch oven.

title: grandma's easy pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until pie begins to turn brown (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Mix spices in a bowl.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add spices to melted butter.
Over high heat, add shrimp and cook until shrimp is pink, about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Serve hot with French bread. Dip bread in sauce.

title: our best baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours, on high setting for 2 to 3 hours.

title: kathryn's venison
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 10 compact rolls, approximately 12-inches long (1 pound each).
Place the rolls on a wire rack with a drip pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except crumbs and add to broccoli.
Put in baking dish; top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: orange walnut salad
directions: Combine lettuce, spinach, oranges and onion in a large bowl. In a saucepan, saut walnuts in butter until lightly browned. Add to lettuce mixture. Toss with Sweet-and-Sour Dressing. Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet tater pone
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. In a mixing bowl, combine sweet potatoes, nutmeg, sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
Add the milk and egg. Pour into the prepared baking dish and sprinkle with remaining pecans. Dot with butter. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: texas turtles
directions: Put unwrapped caramel squares and butter in a double boiler; melt.
Add pecan halves to caramel; take off fire.
Mold into 1-inch patties; lay on buttered aluminum foil to cool.

title: crispy baked fish
directions: Dip
fillet
in
oleo and lemon juice; press in cracker crumbs.
Spray
cookie
sheet
with low-fat spray to keep fish from sticking.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel carrots, sliced.
Cook until tender.
Slice onions and break apart in rings.
Dice bell pepper.
Place cooked carrots in large dish with bell peppers and onions in layers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper each layer.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over layered carrots and onions.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 12 hours before serving.

title: white chocolate-coconut cake
directions: Combine chocolate and water in top of double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook, stirring constantly, until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat; cool.
Cream butter; gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in white chocolate mixture.
Combine 2 1/4 cups flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Combine almonds and coconut; dredge with 1/4 cup flour, stirring to coat well.
Stir into batter.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until soft peaks form; add 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.

title: pineapple upside-down microwave cake
directions: Line bottom of 9-inch round baking dish with wax paper.
Place butter in dish.
Microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds or until butter melts.
Blend in brown sugar and half and half, stirring once.
Arrange pineapple slices and cherries on brown sugar mixture.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make amount of liquid cake box calls for.
Prepare cake mix as package directs using diluted pineapple juice for liquid.
Over fruit in dish pour cake mix (batter).
Place on saucer in oven.
Microwave at power 5 for 6 minutes, rotating dish once.
Increase power to High for 3 to 5 minutes longer, or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: toasted herb rice
directions: Measure rice into ovenproof casserole that has a lid.
Place into oven set at 325°.
Roast for 20 minutes or until rice is toasted and golden.
Remove from oven. Add butter to rice and stir until melted. Pour boiling broth and water over rice.
Stir. Cover, return to oven and bake 30 minutes or until rice is done and has absorbed all of the liquid.
Stir in finely chopped green onions, soy sauce and herb of your choice.

title: quick fruit dip(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve with assorted fresh fruits.
Yields 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: super pickles
directions: Mix all well in a big bowl.
Let stand until sugar dissolves. Put in jars and refrigerate at least 3 days, the longer the better. You can use more or less sugar.
I use 1 3/4 cups.
The more sugar, the crispier.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Place next three ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil; then add to dry ingredients.
Mix next three ingredients and add to rest of batter.
Pour into jelly-roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray an 8-inch round pan with olive oil flavored non-stick spray. Slice eggplant into 1/2-inch thick rounds and layer eggplant and tomato slices in prepared pan. Spread the pasta sauce over vegetables. Cover with foil and bake 20-25 minutes until eggplant is fork tender. Uncover, sprinkle with mozzarella and parmesan cheese and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until cheese is golden. Cut into wedges. Makes 4 servings.

title: california bread
directions: Cut one loaf of French bread in half (lengthwise).
Spread mixture evenly over both halves of bread.
Bake (buttered side up) on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 325°.
Remove.
Let cool a few minutes.
Cut in slices.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake or boil chicken; debone.
Combine chicken and 1 can of cream of chicken soup.
Place in bottom of casserole dish, then combine other can of soup and sour cream. Place on top for next layer. Crumble crackers for topping.
Slice butter on top of it. Sprinkle with poppy or sesame seed.
Cook at 325° or 350° until brown.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, and vinegar or apple cider in
medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and combine with apples, pineapple, peanuts and cool whip. Store in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
This is a double batch.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cool as a cucumber salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumbers, mixing well. Pour over cucumbers. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 muffin tins.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine yogurt with baking soda.
Set aside.
Beat egg in a third bowl, then add the oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir to combine.
Add flour mixture and yogurt mixture alternately to egg mixture.
Gently fold in berries.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned on top.
Cool for 5 minutes, then remove from tins and cool on rack.

title: easy fast microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in bowl (microwave-safe).
Add butter and milk.
Put in microwave for 1 minute and 45 seconds (or until butter is melted).
Add the remaining ingredients; mix fast, as it starts to harden.
Put into small square pan.
Place in refrigerator until hard, then cut into small squares.
This is so good, and so easy!

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Mix pancake batter as directed.
Take skin from chicken.
Cut into bite-size hunks.
No bones.
Heat oil.
Dip chicken pieces into pancake batter until coated.
Gently put into hot oil; turn occasionally.
Cook until browned.

title: yogurt pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix yogurt and Cool Whip together by stirring.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze pie for at least 2 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: best ever apple dumplings
directions: Stir until dough cleans bowl.
Roll out and cut 6 squares put apple, sugar, cinnamon, on each square, place in oblong pan 8 x 12.

title: blizzard chili beans
directions: Brown meat, garlic salt and onions. Drain fat. Add all remaining ingredients. Mix well. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 1/2 hours. Serve with corn chips or corn bread. Enjoy!

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix the picante sauce into the refried beans and spread this into an 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls with floured fingers.
Place on baking sheet (ungreased); press lightly with fork to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks. Store in airtight container.
Keeps well ahead of time.
Yields 6 1/2 to 7 dozen.

title: southwestern stew
directions: Brown hamburger with celery, onion and bell pepper.
Drain and put in crock-pot or soup pot on stove.
Add remaining ingredients. It seems too thick at this point, but don't be fooled and add water.
It "loosens" as it cooks.
You can cook this stew all day in the crock-pot (the mixture fills it almost to the top) or simmer on the stove in a pot for 30 to 40 minutes.
Great with cornbread.

title: rocky road fudge pops
directions: You will also need 12 plastic (3 ounce) cups and 12 popsicle sticks.

title: punch(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Mix water, Jell-O and sugar until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice, stirring constantly.
Add water to make a gallon.
Freeze.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Combine chicken, green onion, cumin, oregano and salt in a large saucepan.
Stir in 2/3 cup salsa.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of the mixture in the center of tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese on each, then fold in left and right sides of tortilla to enclosed filling.
Fold up top and bottom edges making a square.
Place folded side down in a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2 -inch baking dish.
Bake at 475° for 13 minutes.
Heat remaining salsa and pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and add a dollop of sour cream.

title: butterball cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, butter, chopped walnuts and salt until well blended.
Scoop out by rounded teaspoonfuls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 15 minutes or until firm.
Do not overbake.

title: special shrimp pasta salad
directions: Combine all spices with liquid Butter Buds, fat-free mayonnaise and lemon juice; set aside.
Combine shrimp, pasta, green pepper, onion and celery.
Mix mayonnaise mixture together with pasta and shrimp mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 servings, each with 123 calories and 0.7 grams fat.

title: classic white sauce
directions: Mix Argo cornstarch and milk until smooth.
Add Mazola margarine, salt and pepper.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Use for creamed vegetables, meat, poultry, fish or casseroles.
Makes 1 cup.

title: rhubarb dream dessert
directions: Blend and press in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Beat butter, sugar and egg, then add pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and glaze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add other ingredients.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; beat well.
Add one egg yolk at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add milk and flour.
Add about 1/3 of each at a time.
Beat well after adding each one.
Begin with flour and end with flour.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: grits and cheese casserole
directions: Boil water, salt and grits until thick.
Add oleo and cheese. Beat the eggs and put in a measuring cup and finish filling to the 1 cup line with milk.
Add this to the grit mixture and mix well. Put in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: reuben appetizer
directions: Mix together and place in pie plate.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and dish is hot throughout, 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot with party rye bread or rye crackers.

title: chile con carne
directions: Melt shortening in pan, add onion and beef and brown slightly.
Add seasoning, tomatoes, tomato soup and kidney beans. Cook slowly about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
(If you like your chili HOT, add 1/4 tsp. cayenne pepper and increase black pepper and chili powder.)
Serves 5.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Put everything in a large mixing bowl, stir with a spoon until mixed, then beat 10 minutes with mixer.
Makes three large layers or more thin layers.

title: brandy sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar.
Reduce heat and add vanilla.
Beat eggs and add slowly, stirring to prevent eggs from cooking.
Reduce heat to very low after sugar is melted.
Add brandy; stir briskly.
Refrigerate to keep.
Serve warm over bread pudding.

title: aunt bea's cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts (the juice from the cherries can be substituted for the part of the water).
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk; stir with a fork until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead until smooth.
Roll dough out into a large rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle nutmeg over cherries, then spread cherries over dough.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Dampen the edge of the dough with a little warm water and seal.
Slice dough into about 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar water over dough carefully.
Bake 1 hour.

title: black bean and corn quesadillas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl, mash 1 cup beans with a fork; set aside.
In a large non-stick skillet, heat oil over medium heat until hot.
Add onion, cook 10 to 15 minutes or until softened.
Stir occasionally.
Add corn, chili powder, cumin and remaining whole beans and cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Increase heat to medium-high.
Gradually add spinach, stirring 5 to 6 minutes or until wilted and water evaporates.
Spread mashed beans on one side of 4 tortillas (don't worry if they are dry and won't cover the whole tortilla).
Place on a large cookie sheet, bean side up.
Top tortilla with equal amounts of spinach mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Place remaining tortillas on top of filling.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baker's glaze
directions: Mix in a saucepan first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil. Mix in 1 c. sifted powdered sugar. Pour over cake while hot before it thickens.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Soften the cream cheese to room temperature.
Blend together the white vinegar, light cream and curry powder.
Add the cream cheese and work the mixture into a smooth paste.
Stir in the chutney and refrigerate for several hours or overnight if possible.
About 1 hour before serving, stuff the mixture into the celery ribs and cut them into 1 inch pieces.

title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook and stir green onion and garlic in margarine and oil 1 minute.
Add shrimp; cook and stir until shrimp are pink.
Add lemon juice and salt; heat through.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Break lettuce into small pieces and toss with tomatoes, beans, cheese and onions.
Just before serving, add dressing and chips.

title: toffee crisps
directions: Parchment paper is required to bake the cookies on.
These cookies are famous for sticking otherwise.
Preheat oven at 375°. Cream butter and add sugar, vanilla and egg; beat until light. Add sifted dry ingredients and Heath chips.
Drop by 1/2 tsp on parchment paper covered cookie sheet.
Bake on parchment paper about 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool about 1/2 minute, remove to wax paper to cool further.
Makes about 5 to 8 dozen.
Store in airtight container.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients except vanilla and bring to a boil on a low heat.
Must be thick.
Add vanilla.
Let cool.

title: popeye biscuits
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and knead.
Melt the oleo in a pan.
Roll out and cut biscuits; place in pan.
Bake at 475° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brush melted butter on tops.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and onion until tender and drain.
Melt cheese and butter together.
Combine with carrot and onion mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with crushed corn flakes or Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prune puree
directions: Combine prunes and water in food processor or blender.
Makes 1 cup.

title: lemon dump cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, margarine and Crisco in a mixing bowl.
Add the flavoring and milk and beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, while beating.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for one hour and ten minutes to one hour and twenty minutes at 325°.
Let cool in pan, right side up.

title: panned liver and bacon
directions: Cook bacon and set aside.
Brown onions in bacon grease.
Dip liver in flour, salt, pepper and dash of cloves.
Brown in bacon grease.
Add Worcestershire sauce, water and parsley.
Crumble bacon over liver.
Put in onions and simmer 15 minutes.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Pour into a 13 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost while cake is still warm.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers.
In a deep bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add cucumber slices.
Cover with plate and a weight.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Drain slices to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Bake in unbaked pie crust for 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: oatmeal sheet cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients and set aside in covered bowl. Mix together the sugars, baking powder, soda, vanilla, eggs, salt, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add the oat mixture and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured sheet cake pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Leave unfrosted or you can add a light buttercream frosting.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot overnight on low with an onion. Remove from crock-pot and save 1 cup of broth.
After roast has cooled, shred and put back into crock-pot.
Add brown sugar, barbecue sauce, broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Let simmer 2 hours in crock-pot.
This makes wonderful barbecue sandwiches.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Melt butter, oil and marshmallows in a large bowl.
Mix popcorn, peanuts and M&M's.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn mixture and stir to coat.
Mash into Bundt pan.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Turn out on platter and slice.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Mix sugar, water and spices.
Boil 10 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour in a warm place.
Strain.
When ready to serve, add juice and cider.
Heat quickly to boiling point.
Pour over crab apples or small oranges, studded with cloves, in a punch bowl.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Press garlic and cook until golden.
Add clam juice from cans; add salt, pepper and thyme.
Let simmer very slowly.
Add clams.
Cook linguine.
Add parsley to sauce about 5 minutes before linguine is cooked.
Drain linguine and mix all together.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: rumanian ghivetch(vegetable stew)
directions: Arrange the vegetable in layers in 3 to 4 quart ungreased casserole and sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Heat together the bouillon, olive oil and garlic.
Add to the casserole.
Sprinkle the dill over the top.
Cover the casserole and bake at 350° until all the vegetables are tender, one hour or longer.
Serve lukewarm rather than piping hot.
Serves 6 to 8. Feel free to substitute vegetables you may prefer.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir water and mix until moistened. Dust countertop, rolling pin and bottom of glass with flour. Knead 10 times with fingers and palms of hands.
Roll out with pin and cut with glass.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate until chilled.
Beat mixture with electric mixer and add Cool Whip.
Continue beating until well blended.
Pour into 10-inch baked pie shell.
Let stand overnight.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: block and tackle macaroni bake
directions: After thawing and draining broccoli, cut into 1-inch pieces. Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed. Combine cream cheese and sour cream; keep separate.
In greased casserole dish, layer beef mixture, noodles and cream cheese mixture until finished.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water (about 2 minutes).
Add other ingredients with fork.
Chopped celery and nuts are optional. Serves 8.

title: sweet-sour stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a plastic or paper bag.
Add meat; shake to coat.
In large skillet, brown meat well in hot shortening.
Combine water, ketchup, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add onion to taste.
Stir in browned meat.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook 45 minutes more or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cut asparagus in thirds.
Flavor cream sauce with Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Put all ingredients together in layers in a casserole dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
May be kept in refrigerator 3 days.
Serve with crackers or Doritos.
Serves 12.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Beat egg, sugar and vanilla.
Mix baking powder, flour and salt.
Combine and add apples and nuts.
Grease pie plate.
Pour in mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: consomme madrilene
directions: Heat consomme Madrilene and lemon juice just to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Serve in mugs with slices of lemon.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Stir in salt, pepper and pimento.
Spoon 1/4 cup white sauce into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half each of potatoes, onions, remaining sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers, using remaining potatoes, onions and sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until tender.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: coffee chocolate almond mousse
directions: Put the first five ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High until marshmallows melt.
Stir in the cocoa powder.
Cool completely.
When cool, fold in the whipped cream. Place in a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Garnish with chocolate curls.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, olives, dressing and chili powder.
Layer half each of the meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers. Bake 20 minutes.
